2099 void Simulator::VisitLoadStorePreIndex(Instruction* instr) {
2100  LoadStoreHelper(instr, instr->ImmLS(), PreIndex);
2101 }
2102 
2103 void Simulator::VisitLoadStorePostIndex(Instruction* instr) {
2104  LoadStoreHelper(instr, instr->ImmLS(), PostIndex);
2105 }
2106 
2107 void Simulator::VisitLoadStoreRegisterOffset(Instruction* instr) {
2108  Extend ext = static_cast<Extend>(instr->ExtendMode());
2109  DCHECK((ext == UXTW) || (ext == UXTX) || (ext == SXTW) || (ext == SXTX));
2110  unsigned shift_amount = instr->ImmShiftLS() * instr->SizeLS();
2111 
2112  int64_t offset = ExtendValue(xreg(instr->Rm()), ext, shift_amount);
2113  LoadStoreHelper(instr, offset, Offset);
2114 }
2115 
2116 void Simulator::LoadStoreHelper(Instruction* instr, int64_t offset,
2117  AddrMode addrmode) {
2118  unsigned srcdst = instr->Rt();
2119  unsigned addr_reg = instr->Rn();
2120  uintptr_t address = LoadStoreAddress(addr_reg, offset, addrmode);
2121  uintptr_t stack = 0;
2122 
2123  unsigned access_size = 1 << instr->SizeLS();
2124  // First, check whether the memory is accessible (for wasm trap handling).
2125  if (!ProbeMemory(address, access_size)) return;
2126 
2127  {
2128  GlobalMonitor::SimulatorMutex lock_guard(global_monitor_);
2129  if (instr->IsLoad()) {
2130  local_monitor_.NotifyLoad();
2131  } else {
2132  local_monitor_.NotifyStore();
2133  global_monitor_->NotifyStore_Locked(&global_monitor_processor_);
2134  }
2135  }
2136 
2137  // Handle the writeback for stores before the store. On a CPU the writeback
2138  // and the store are atomic, but when running on the simulator it is possible
2139  // to be interrupted in between. The simulator is not thread safe and V8 does
2140  // not require it to be to run JavaScript therefore the profiler may sample
2141  // the "simulated" CPU in the middle of load/store with writeback. The code
2142  // below ensures that push operations are safe even when interrupted: the
2143  // stack pointer will be decremented before adding an element to the stack.
2144  if (instr->IsStore()) {
2145  LoadStoreWriteBack(addr_reg, offset, addrmode);
2146 
2147  // For store the address post writeback is used to check access below the
2148  // stack.
2149  stack = sp();
2150  }
2151 
2152  LoadStoreOp op = static_cast<LoadStoreOp>(instr->Mask(LoadStoreMask));
2153  switch (op) {
2154  // Use _no_log variants to suppress the register trace (LOG_REGS,
2155  // LOG_VREGS). We will print a more detailed log.
2156  case LDRB_w:
2157  set_wreg_no_log(srcdst, MemoryRead<uint8_t>(address));
2158  break;
2159  case LDRH_w:
2160  set_wreg_no_log(srcdst, MemoryRead<uint16_t>(address));
2161  break;
2162  case LDR_w:
2163  set_wreg_no_log(srcdst, MemoryRead<uint32_t>(address));
2164  break;
2165  case LDR_x:
2166  set_xreg_no_log(srcdst, MemoryRead<uint64_t>(address));
2167  break;
2168  case LDRSB_w:
2169  set_wreg_no_log(srcdst, MemoryRead<int8_t>(address));
2170  break;
2171  case LDRSH_w:
2172  set_wreg_no_log(srcdst, MemoryRead<int16_t>(address));
2173  break;
2174  case LDRSB_x:
2175  set_xreg_no_log(srcdst, MemoryRead<int8_t>(address));
2176  break;
2177  case LDRSH_x:
2178  set_xreg_no_log(srcdst, MemoryRead<int16_t>(address));
2179  break;
2180  case LDRSW_x:
2181  set_xreg_no_log(srcdst, MemoryRead<int32_t>(address));
2182  break;
2183  case LDR_b:
2184  set_breg_no_log(srcdst, MemoryRead<uint8_t>(address));
2185  break;
2186  case LDR_h:
2187  set_hreg_no_log(srcdst, MemoryRead<uint16_t>(address));
2188  break;
2189  case LDR_s:
2190  set_sreg_no_log(srcdst, MemoryRead<float>(address));
2191  break;
2192  case LDR_d:
2193  set_dreg_no_log(srcdst, MemoryRead<double>(address));
2194  break;
2195  case LDR_q:
2196  set_qreg_no_log(srcdst, MemoryRead<qreg_t>(address));
2197  break;
2198 
2199  case STRB_w:
2200  MemoryWrite<uint8_t>(address, wreg(srcdst));
2201  break;
2202  case STRH_w:
2203  MemoryWrite<uint16_t>(address, wreg(srcdst));
2204  break;
2205  case STR_w:
2206  MemoryWrite<uint32_t>(address, wreg(srcdst));
2207  break;
2208  case STR_x:
2209  MemoryWrite<uint64_t>(address, xreg(srcdst));
2210  break;
2211  case STR_b:
2212  MemoryWrite<uint8_t>(address, breg(srcdst));
2213  break;
2214  case STR_h:
2215  MemoryWrite<uint16_t>(address, hreg(srcdst));
2216  break;
2217  case STR_s:
2218  MemoryWrite<float>(address, sreg(srcdst));
2219  break;
2220  case STR_d:
2221  MemoryWrite<double>(address, dreg(srcdst));
2222  break;
2223  case STR_q:
2224  MemoryWrite<qreg_t>(address, qreg(srcdst));
2225  break;
2226 
2227  default:
2228  UNIMPLEMENTED();
2229  }
2230 
2231  // Print a detailed trace (including the memory address) instead of the basic
2232  // register:value trace generated by set_*reg().
2233  if (instr->IsLoad()) {
2234  if ((op == LDR_s) || (op == LDR_d)) {
2235  LogVRead(address, srcdst, GetPrintRegisterFormatForSizeFP(access_size));
2236  } else if ((op == LDR_b) || (op == LDR_h) || (op == LDR_q)) {
2237  LogVRead(address, srcdst, GetPrintRegisterFormatForSize(access_size));
2238  } else {
2239  LogRead(address, srcdst, GetPrintRegisterFormatForSize(access_size));
2240  }
2241  } else {
2242  if ((op == STR_s) || (op == STR_d)) {
2243  LogVWrite(address, srcdst, GetPrintRegisterFormatForSizeFP(access_size));
2244  } else if ((op == STR_b) || (op == STR_h) || (op == STR_q)) {
2245  LogVWrite(address, srcdst, GetPrintRegisterFormatForSize(access_size));
2246  } else {
2247  LogWrite(address, srcdst, GetPrintRegisterFormatForSize(access_size));
2248  }
2249  }
2250 
2251  // Handle the writeback for loads after the load to ensure safe pop
2252  // operation even when interrupted in the middle of it. The stack pointer
2253  // is only updated after the load so pop(fp) will never break the invariant
2254  // sp <= fp expected while walking the stack in the sampler.
2255  if (instr->IsLoad()) {
2256  // For loads the address pre writeback is used to check access below the
2257  // stack.
2258  stack = sp();
2259 
2260  LoadStoreWriteBack(addr_reg, offset, addrmode);
2261  }
2262 
2263  // Accesses below the stack pointer (but above the platform stack limit) are
2264  // not allowed in the ABI.
2265  CheckMemoryAccess(address, stack);
2266 }
2267 
2268 void Simulator::VisitLoadStorePairOffset(Instruction* instr) {
2269  LoadStorePairHelper(instr, Offset);
2270 }
2271 
2272 void Simulator::VisitLoadStorePairPreIndex(Instruction* instr) {
2273  LoadStorePairHelper(instr, PreIndex);
2274 }
2275 
2276 void Simulator::VisitLoadStorePairPostIndex(Instruction* instr) {
2277  LoadStorePairHelper(instr, PostIndex);
2278 }
2279 
2280 void Simulator::LoadStorePairHelper(Instruction* instr, AddrMode addrmode) {
2281  unsigned rt = instr->Rt();
2282  unsigned rt2 = instr->Rt2();
2283  unsigned addr_reg = instr->Rn();
2284  size_t access_size = 1ULL << instr->SizeLSPair();
2285  int64_t offset = instr->ImmLSPair() * access_size;
2286  uintptr_t address = LoadStoreAddress(addr_reg, offset, addrmode);
2287  uintptr_t address2 = address + access_size;
2288  uintptr_t stack = 0;
2289 
2290  {
2291  GlobalMonitor::SimulatorMutex lock_guard(global_monitor_);
2292  if (instr->IsLoad()) {
2293  local_monitor_.NotifyLoad();
2294  } else {
2295  local_monitor_.NotifyStore();
2296  global_monitor_->NotifyStore_Locked(&global_monitor_processor_);
2297  }
2298  }
2299 
2300  // Handle the writeback for stores before the store. On a CPU the writeback
2301  // and the store are atomic, but when running on the simulator it is possible
2302  // to be interrupted in between. The simulator is not thread safe and V8 does
2303  // not require it to be to run JavaScript therefore the profiler may sample
2304  // the "simulated" CPU in the middle of load/store with writeback. The code
2305  // below ensures that push operations are safe even when interrupted: the
2306  // stack pointer will be decremented before adding an element to the stack.
2307  if (instr->IsStore()) {
2308  LoadStoreWriteBack(addr_reg, offset, addrmode);
2309 
2310  // For store the address post writeback is used to check access below the
2311  // stack.
2312  stack = sp();
2313  }
2314 
2315  LoadStorePairOp op =
2316  static_cast<LoadStorePairOp>(instr->Mask(LoadStorePairMask));
2317 
2318  // 'rt' and 'rt2' can only be aliased for stores.
2319  DCHECK(((op & LoadStorePairLBit) == 0) || (rt != rt2));
2320 
2321  switch (op) {
2322  // Use _no_log variants to suppress the register trace (LOG_REGS,
2323  // LOG_VREGS). We will print a more detailed log.
2324  case LDP_w: {
2325  DCHECK_EQ(access_size, static_cast<unsigned>(kWRegSize));
2326  set_wreg_no_log(rt, MemoryRead<uint32_t>(address));
2327  set_wreg_no_log(rt2, MemoryRead<uint32_t>(address2));
2328  break;
2329  }
2330  case LDP_s: {
2331  DCHECK_EQ(access_size, static_cast<unsigned>(kSRegSize));
2332  set_sreg_no_log(rt, MemoryRead<float>(address));
2333  set_sreg_no_log(rt2, MemoryRead<float>(address2));
2334  break;
2335  }
2336  case LDP_x: {
2337  DCHECK_EQ(access_size, static_cast<unsigned>(kXRegSize));
2338  set_xreg_no_log(rt, MemoryRead<uint64_t>(address));
2339  set_xreg_no_log(rt2, MemoryRead<uint64_t>(address2));
2340  break;
2341  }
2342  case LDP_d: {
2343  DCHECK_EQ(access_size, static_cast<unsigned>(kDRegSize));
2344  set_dreg_no_log(rt, MemoryRead<double>(address));
2345  set_dreg_no_log(rt2, MemoryRead<double>(address2));
2346  break;
2347  }
2348  case LDP_q: {
2349  DCHECK_EQ(access_size, static_cast<unsigned>(kQRegSize));
2350  set_qreg(rt, MemoryRead<qreg_t>(address), NoRegLog);
2351  set_qreg(rt2, MemoryRead<qreg_t>(address2), NoRegLog);
2352  break;
2353  }
2354  case LDPSW_x: {
2355  DCHECK_EQ(access_size, static_cast<unsigned>(kWRegSize));
2356  set_xreg_no_log(rt, MemoryRead<int32_t>(address));
2357  set_xreg_no_log(rt2, MemoryRead<int32_t>(address2));
2358  break;
2359  }
2360  case STP_w: {
2361  DCHECK_EQ(access_size, static_cast<unsigned>(kWRegSize));
2362  MemoryWrite<uint32_t>(address, wreg(rt));
2363  MemoryWrite<uint32_t>(address2, wreg(rt2));
2364  break;
2365  }
2366  case STP_s: {
2367  DCHECK_EQ(access_size, static_cast<unsigned>(kSRegSize));
2368  MemoryWrite<float>(address, sreg(rt));
2369  MemoryWrite<float>(address2, sreg(rt2));
2370  break;
2371  }
2372  case STP_x: {
2373  DCHECK_EQ(access_size, static_cast<unsigned>(kXRegSize));
2374  MemoryWrite<uint64_t>(address, xreg(rt));
2375  MemoryWrite<uint64_t>(address2, xreg(rt2));
2376  break;
2377  }
2378  case STP_d: {
2379  DCHECK_EQ(access_size, static_cast<unsigned>(kDRegSize));
2380  MemoryWrite<double>(address, dreg(rt));
2381  MemoryWrite<double>(address2, dreg(rt2));
2382  break;
2383  }
2384  case STP_q: {
2385  DCHECK_EQ(access_size, static_cast<unsigned>(kQRegSize));
2386  MemoryWrite<qreg_t>(address, qreg(rt));
2387  MemoryWrite<qreg_t>(address2, qreg(rt2));
2388  break;
2389  }
2390  default:
2391  UNREACHABLE();
2392  }
2393 
2394  // Print a detailed trace (including the memory address) instead of the basic
2395  // register:value trace generated by set_*reg().
2396  if (instr->IsLoad()) {
2397  if ((op == LDP_s) || (op == LDP_d)) {
2398  LogVRead(address, rt, GetPrintRegisterFormatForSizeFP(access_size));
2399  LogVRead(address2, rt2, GetPrintRegisterFormatForSizeFP(access_size));
2400  } else if (op == LDP_q) {
2401  LogVRead(address, rt, GetPrintRegisterFormatForSize(access_size));
2402  LogVRead(address2, rt2, GetPrintRegisterFormatForSize(access_size));
2403  } else {
2404  LogRead(address, rt, GetPrintRegisterFormatForSize(access_size));
2405  LogRead(address2, rt2, GetPrintRegisterFormatForSize(access_size));
2406  }
2407  } else {
2408  if ((op == STP_s) || (op == STP_d)) {
2409  LogVWrite(address, rt, GetPrintRegisterFormatForSizeFP(access_size));
2410  LogVWrite(address2, rt2, GetPrintRegisterFormatForSizeFP(access_size));
2411  } else if (op == STP_q) {
2412  LogVWrite(address, rt, GetPrintRegisterFormatForSize(access_size));
2413  LogVWrite(address2, rt2, GetPrintRegisterFormatForSize(access_size));
2414  } else {
2415  LogWrite(address, rt, GetPrintRegisterFormatForSize(access_size));
2416  LogWrite(address2, rt2, GetPrintRegisterFormatForSize(access_size));
2417  }
2418  }
2419 
2420  // Handle the writeback for loads after the load to ensure safe pop
2421  // operation even when interrupted in the middle of it. The stack pointer
2422  // is only updated after the load so pop(fp) will never break the invariant
2423  // sp <= fp expected while walking the stack in the sampler.
2424  if (instr->IsLoad()) {
2425  // For loads the address pre writeback is used to check access below the
2426  // stack.
2427  stack = sp();
2428 
2429  LoadStoreWriteBack(addr_reg, offset, addrmode);
2430  }
2431 
2432  // Accesses below the stack pointer (but above the platform stack limit) are
2433  // not allowed in the ABI.
2434  CheckMemoryAccess(address, stack);
2435 }
2436 
2437 void Simulator::VisitLoadLiteral(Instruction* instr) {
2438  uintptr_t address = instr->LiteralAddress();
2439  unsigned rt = instr->Rt();
2440 
2441  {
2442  GlobalMonitor::SimulatorMutex lock_guard(global_monitor_);
2443  local_monitor_.NotifyLoad();
2444  }
2445 
2446  switch (instr->Mask(LoadLiteralMask)) {
2447  // Use _no_log variants to suppress the register trace (LOG_REGS,
2448  // LOG_VREGS), then print a more detailed log.
2449  case LDR_w_lit:
2450  set_wreg_no_log(rt, MemoryRead<uint32_t>(address));
2451  LogRead(address, rt, kPrintWReg);
2452  break;
2453  case LDR_x_lit:
2454  set_xreg_no_log(rt, MemoryRead<uint64_t>(address));
2455  LogRead(address, rt, kPrintXReg);
2456  break;
2457  case LDR_s_lit:
2458  set_sreg_no_log(rt, MemoryRead<float>(address));
2459  LogVRead(address, rt, kPrintSReg);
2460  break;
2461  case LDR_d_lit:
2462  set_dreg_no_log(rt, MemoryRead<double>(address));
2463  LogVRead(address, rt, kPrintDReg);
2464  break;
2465  default:
2466  UNREACHABLE();
2467  }
2468 }
2469 
2470 uintptr_t Simulator::LoadStoreAddress(unsigned addr_reg, int64_t offset,
2471  AddrMode addrmode) {
2472  const unsigned kSPRegCode = kSPRegInternalCode & kRegCodeMask;
2473  uint64_t address = xreg(addr_reg, Reg31IsStackPointer);
2474  if ((addr_reg == kSPRegCode) && ((address % 16) != 0)) {
2475  // When the base register is SP the stack pointer is required to be
2476  // quadword aligned prior to the address calculation and write-backs.
2477  // Misalignment will cause a stack alignment fault.
2478  FATAL("ALIGNMENT EXCEPTION");
2479  }
2480 
2481  if ((addrmode == Offset) || (addrmode == PreIndex)) {
2482  address += offset;
2483  }
2484 
2485  return address;
2486 }
2487 
2488 void Simulator::LoadStoreWriteBack(unsigned addr_reg, int64_t offset,
2489  AddrMode addrmode) {
2490  if ((addrmode == PreIndex) || (addrmode == PostIndex)) {
2491  DCHECK_NE(offset, 0);
2492  uint64_t address = xreg(addr_reg, Reg31IsStackPointer);
2493  set_reg(addr_reg, address + offset, Reg31IsStackPointer);
2494  }
2495 }
2496 
2497 Simulator::TransactionSize Simulator::get_transaction_size(unsigned size) {
2498  switch (size) {
2499  case 0:
2500  return TransactionSize::None;
2501  case 1:
2502  return TransactionSize::Byte;
2503  case 2:
2504  return TransactionSize::HalfWord;
2505  case 4:
2506  return TransactionSize::Word;
2507  case 8:
2508  return TransactionSize::DoubleWord;
2509  default:
2510  UNREACHABLE();
2511  }
2512 }
2513 
2514 void Simulator::VisitLoadStoreAcquireRelease(Instruction* instr) {
2515  unsigned rt = instr->Rt();
2516  unsigned rn = instr->Rn();
2517  LoadStoreAcquireReleaseOp op = static_cast<LoadStoreAcquireReleaseOp>(
2518  instr->Mask(LoadStoreAcquireReleaseMask));
2519 
2520  switch (op) {
2521  case CAS_w:
2522  case CASA_w:
2523  case CASL_w:
2524  case CASAL_w:
2525  CompareAndSwapHelper<uint32_t>(instr);
2526  return;
2527  case CAS_x:
2528  case CASA_x:
2529  case CASL_x:
2530  case CASAL_x:
2531  CompareAndSwapHelper<uint64_t>(instr);
2532  return;
2533  case CASB:
2534  case CASAB:
2535  case CASLB:
2536  case CASALB:
2537  CompareAndSwapHelper<uint8_t>(instr);
2538  return;
2539  case CASH:
2540  case CASAH:
2541  case CASLH:
2542  case CASALH:
2543  CompareAndSwapHelper<uint16_t>(instr);
2544  return;
2545  case CASP_w:
2546  case CASPA_w:
2547  case CASPL_w:
2548  case CASPAL_w:
2549  CompareAndSwapPairHelper<uint32_t>(instr);
2550  return;
2551  case CASP_x:
2552  case CASPA_x:
2553  case CASPL_x:
2554  case CASPAL_x:
2555  CompareAndSwapPairHelper<uint64_t>(instr);
2556  return;
2557  default:
2558  break;
2559  }
2560 
2561  int32_t is_acquire_release = instr->LoadStoreXAcquireRelease();
2562  int32_t is_exclusive = (instr->LoadStoreXNotExclusive() == 0);
2563  int32_t is_load = instr->LoadStoreXLoad();
2564  int32_t is_pair = instr->LoadStoreXPair();
2565  USE(is_acquire_release);
2566  USE(is_pair);
2567  DCHECK_NE(is_acquire_release, 0); // Non-acquire/release unimplemented.
2568  DCHECK_EQ(is_pair, 0); // Pair unimplemented.
2569  unsigned access_size = 1 << instr->LoadStoreXSizeLog2();
2570  uintptr_t address = LoadStoreAddress(rn, 0, AddrMode::Offset);
2571  DCHECK_EQ(address % access_size, 0);
2572  // First, check whether the memory is accessible (for wasm trap handling).
2573  if (!ProbeMemory(address, access_size)) return;
2574  GlobalMonitor::SimulatorMutex lock_guard(global_monitor_);
2575 
2576  if (is_load != 0) {
2577  if (is_exclusive) {
2578  local_monitor_.NotifyLoadExcl(address, get_transaction_size(access_size));
2579  global_monitor_->NotifyLoadExcl_Locked(address,
2580  &global_monitor_processor_);
2581  } else {
2582  local_monitor_.NotifyLoad();
2583  }
2584  switch (op) {
2585  case LDAR_b:
2586  case LDAXR_b:
2587  set_wreg_no_log(rt, MemoryRead<uint8_t>(address));
2588  break;
2589  case LDAR_h:
2590  case LDAXR_h:
2591  set_wreg_no_log(rt, MemoryRead<uint16_t>(address));
2592  break;
2593  case LDAR_w:
2594  case LDAXR_w:
2595  set_wreg_no_log(rt, MemoryRead<uint32_t>(address));
2596  break;
2597  case LDAR_x:
2598  case LDAXR_x:
2599  set_xreg_no_log(rt, MemoryRead<uint64_t>(address));
2600  break;
2601  default:
2602  UNIMPLEMENTED();
2603  }
2604  LogRead(address, rt, GetPrintRegisterFormatForSize(access_size));
2605  } else {
2606  if (is_exclusive) {
2607  unsigned rs = instr->Rs();
2608  DCHECK_NE(rs, rt);
2609  DCHECK_NE(rs, rn);
2610  if (local_monitor_.NotifyStoreExcl(address,
2611  get_transaction_size(access_size)) &&
2612  global_monitor_->NotifyStoreExcl_Locked(address,
2613  &global_monitor_processor_)) {
2614  switch (op) {
2615  case STLXR_b:
2616  MemoryWrite<uint8_t>(address, wreg(rt));
2617  break;
2618  case STLXR_h:
2619  MemoryWrite<uint16_t>(address, wreg(rt));
2620  break;
2621  case STLXR_w:
2622  MemoryWrite<uint32_t>(address, wreg(rt));
2623  break;
2624  case STLXR_x:
2625  MemoryWrite<uint64_t>(address, xreg(rt));
2626  break;
2627  default:
2628  UNIMPLEMENTED();
2629  }
2630  LogWrite(address, rt, GetPrintRegisterFormatForSize(access_size));
2631  set_wreg(rs, 0);
2632  } else {
2633  set_wreg(rs, 1);
2634  }
2635  } else {
2636  local_monitor_.NotifyStore();
2637  global_monitor_->NotifyStore_Locked(&global_monitor_processor_);
2638  switch (op) {
2639  case STLR_b:
2640  MemoryWrite<uint8_t>(address, wreg(rt));
2641  break;
2642  case STLR_h:
2643  MemoryWrite<uint16_t>(address, wreg(rt));
2644  break;
2645  case STLR_w:
2646  MemoryWrite<uint32_t>(address, wreg(rt));
2647  break;
2648  case STLR_x:
2649  MemoryWrite<uint64_t>(address, xreg(rt));
2650  break;
2651  default:
2652  UNIMPLEMENTED();
2653  }
2654  }
2655  }
2656 }
2657 
2658 template <typename T>
2659 void Simulator::CompareAndSwapHelper(const Instruction* instr) {
2660  unsigned rs = instr->Rs();
2661  unsigned rt = instr->Rt();
2662  unsigned rn = instr->Rn();
2663 
2664  unsigned element_size = sizeof(T);
2665  uint64_t address = reg<uint64_t>(rn, Reg31IsStackPointer);
2666 
2667  // First, check whether the memory is accessible (for wasm trap handling).
2668  if (!ProbeMemory(address, element_size)) return;
2669 
2670  bool is_acquire = instr->Bit(22) == 1;
2671  bool is_release = instr->Bit(15) == 1;
2672 
2673  T comparevalue = reg<T>(rs);
2674  T newvalue = reg<T>(rt);
2675 
2676  // The architecture permits that the data read clears any exclusive monitors
2677  // associated with that location, even if the compare subsequently fails.
2678  local_monitor_.NotifyLoad();
2679 
2680  T data = MemoryRead<T>(address);
2681  if (is_acquire) {
2682  // Approximate load-acquire by issuing a full barrier after the load.
2683  std::atomic_thread_fence(std::memory_order_seq_cst);
2684  }
2685 
2686  if (data == comparevalue) {
2687  GlobalMonitor::SimulatorMutex lock_guard(global_monitor_);
2688 
2689  if (is_release) {
2690  local_monitor_.NotifyStore();
2691  global_monitor_->NotifyStore_Locked(&global_monitor_processor_);
2692  // Approximate store-release by issuing a full barrier before the store.
2693  std::atomic_thread_fence(std::memory_order_seq_cst);
2694  }
2695 
2696  MemoryWrite<T>(address, newvalue);
2697  LogWrite(address, rt, GetPrintRegisterFormatForSize(element_size));
2698  }
2699 
2700  set_reg<T>(rs, data);
2701  LogRead(address, rs, GetPrintRegisterFormatForSize(element_size));
2702 }
2703 
2704 template <typename T>
2705 void Simulator::CompareAndSwapPairHelper(const Instruction* instr) {
2706  DCHECK((sizeof(T) == 4) || (sizeof(T) == 8));
2707  unsigned rs = instr->Rs();
2708  unsigned rt = instr->Rt();
2709  unsigned rn = instr->Rn();
2710 
2711  DCHECK((rs % 2 == 0) && (rt % 2 == 0));
2712 
2713  unsigned element_size = sizeof(T);
2714  uint64_t address = reg<uint64_t>(rn, Reg31IsStackPointer);
2715 
2716  uint64_t address2 = address + element_size;
2717 
2718  // First, check whether the memory is accessible (for wasm trap handling).
2719  if (!ProbeMemory(address, element_size)) return;
2720  if (!ProbeMemory(address2, element_size)) return;
2721 
2722  bool is_acquire = instr->Bit(22) == 1;
2723  bool is_release = instr->Bit(15) == 1;
2724 
2725  T comparevalue_high = reg<T>(rs + 1);
2726  T comparevalue_low = reg<T>(rs);
2727  T newvalue_high = reg<T>(rt + 1);
2728  T newvalue_low = reg<T>(rt);
2729 
2730  // The architecture permits that the data read clears any exclusive monitors
2731  // associated with that location, even if the compare subsequently fails.
2732  local_monitor_.NotifyLoad();
2733 
2734  T data_low = MemoryRead<T>(address);
2735  T data_high = MemoryRead<T>(address2);
2736 
2737  if (is_acquire) {
2738  // Approximate load-acquire by issuing a full barrier after the load.
2739  std::atomic_thread_fence(std::memory_order_seq_cst);
2740  }
2741 
2742  bool same =
2743  (data_high == comparevalue_high) && (data_low == comparevalue_low);
2744  if (same) {
2745  GlobalMonitor::SimulatorMutex lock_guard(global_monitor_);
2746 
2747  if (is_release) {
2748  local_monitor_.NotifyStore();
2749  global_monitor_->NotifyStore_Locked(&global_monitor_processor_);
2750  // Approximate store-release by issuing a full barrier before the store.
2751  std::atomic_thread_fence(std::memory_order_seq_cst);
2752  }
2753 
2754  MemoryWrite<T>(address, newvalue_low);
2755  MemoryWrite<T>(address2, newvalue_high);
2756  }
2757 
2758  set_reg<T>(rs + 1, data_high);
2759  set_reg<T>(rs, data_low);
2760 
2761  PrintRegisterFormat format = GetPrintRegisterFormatForSize(element_size);
2762  LogRead(address, rs, format);
2763  LogRead(address2, rs + 1, format);
2764 
2765  if (same) {
2766  LogWrite(address, rt, format);
2767  LogWrite(address2, rt + 1, format);
2768  }
2769 }
2770 
2771 template <typename T>
2772 void Simulator::AtomicMemorySimpleHelper(const Instruction* instr) {
2773  unsigned rs = instr->Rs();
2774  unsigned rt = instr->Rt();
2775  unsigned rn = instr->Rn();
2776 
2777  bool is_acquire = (instr->Bit(23) == 1) && (rt != kZeroRegCode);
2778  bool is_release = instr->Bit(22) == 1;
2779 
2780  unsigned element_size = sizeof(T);
2781  uint64_t address = xreg(rn, Reg31IsStackPointer);
2782  DCHECK_EQ(address % element_size, 0);
2783 
2784  // First, check whether the memory is accessible (for wasm trap handling).
2785  if (!ProbeMemory(address, element_size)) return;
2786 
2787  local_monitor_.NotifyLoad();
2788 
2789  T value = reg<T>(rs);
2790 
2791  T data = MemoryRead<T>(address);
2792 
2793  if (is_acquire) {
2794  // Approximate load-acquire by issuing a full barrier after the load.
2795  std::atomic_thread_fence(std::memory_order_seq_cst);
2796  }
2797 
2798  T result = 0;
2799  switch (instr->Mask(AtomicMemorySimpleOpMask)) {
2800  case LDADDOp:
2801  result = data + value;
2802  break;
2803  case LDCLROp:
2804  DCHECK(!std::numeric_limits<T>::is_signed);
2805  result = data & ~value;
2806  break;
2807  case LDEOROp:
2808  DCHECK(!std::numeric_limits<T>::is_signed);
2809  result = data ^ value;
2810  break;
2811  case LDSETOp:
2812  DCHECK(!std::numeric_limits<T>::is_signed);
2813  result = data | value;
2814  break;
2815 
2816  // Signed/Unsigned difference is done via the templated type T.
2817  case LDSMAXOp:
2818  case LDUMAXOp:
2819  result = (data > value) ? data : value;
2820  break;
2821  case LDSMINOp:
2822  case LDUMINOp:
2823  result = (data > value) ? value : data;
2824  break;
2825  }
2826 
2827  if (is_release) {
2828  GlobalMonitor::SimulatorMutex lock_guard(global_monitor_);
2829  local_monitor_.NotifyStore();
2830  global_monitor_->NotifyStore_Locked(&global_monitor_processor_);
2831  // Approximate store-release by issuing a full barrier before the store.
2832  std::atomic_thread_fence(std::memory_order_seq_cst);
2833  }
2834 
2835  MemoryWrite<T>(address, result);
2836  set_reg<T>(rt, data);
2837 
2838  PrintRegisterFormat format = GetPrintRegisterFormatForSize(element_size);
2839  LogRead(address, rt, format);
2840  LogWrite(address, rs, format);
2841 }
2842 
2843 template <typename T>
2844 void Simulator::AtomicMemorySwapHelper(const Instruction* instr) {
2845  unsigned rs = instr->Rs();
2846  unsigned rt = instr->Rt();
2847  unsigned rn = instr->Rn();
2848 
2849  bool is_acquire = (instr->Bit(23) == 1) && (rt != kZeroRegCode);
2850  bool is_release = instr->Bit(22) == 1;
2851 
2852  unsigned element_size = sizeof(T);
2853  uint64_t address = xreg(rn, Reg31IsStackPointer);
2854 
2855  // First, check whether the memory is accessible (for wasm trap handling).
2856  if (!ProbeMemory(address, element_size)) return;
2857 
2858  local_monitor_.NotifyLoad();
2859 
2860  T data = MemoryRead<T>(address);
2861  if (is_acquire) {
2862  // Approximate load-acquire by issuing a full barrier after the load.
2863  std::atomic_thread_fence(std::memory_order_seq_cst);
2864  }
2865 
2866  if (is_release) {
2867  GlobalMonitor::SimulatorMutex lock_guard(global_monitor_);
2868  local_monitor_.NotifyStore();
2869  global_monitor_->NotifyStore_Locked(&global_monitor_processor_);
2870  // Approximate store-release by issuing a full barrier before the store.
2871  std::atomic_thread_fence(std::memory_order_seq_cst);
2872  }
2873  MemoryWrite<T>(address, reg<T>(rs));
2874 
2875  set_reg<T>(rt, data);
2876 
2877  PrintRegisterFormat format = GetPrintRegisterFormatForSize(element_size);
2878  LogRead(address, rt, format);
2879  LogWrite(address, rs, format);
2880 }
2881 
2882 #define ATOMIC_MEMORY_SIMPLE_UINT_LIST(V) \
2883  V(LDADD) \
2884  V(LDCLR) \
2885  V(LDEOR) \
2886  V(LDSET) \
2887  V(LDUMAX) \
2888  V(LDUMIN)
2889 
2890 #define ATOMIC_MEMORY_SIMPLE_INT_LIST(V) \
2891  V(LDSMAX) \
2892  V(LDSMIN)

2894 void Simulator::VisitAtomicMemory(Instruction* instr) {
2895  switch (instr->Mask(AtomicMemoryMask)) {
2896 // clang-format off
2897 #define SIM_FUNC_B(A) \
2898  case A##B: \
2899  case A##AB: \
2900  case A##LB: \
2901  case A##ALB:
2902 #define SIM_FUNC_H(A) \
2903  case A##H: \
2904  case A##AH: \
2905  case A##LH: \
2906  case A##ALH:
2907 #define SIM_FUNC_w(A) \
2908  case A##_w: \
2909  case A##A_w: \
2910  case A##L_w: \
2911  case A##AL_w:
2912 #define SIM_FUNC_x(A) \
2913  case A##_x: \
2914  case A##A_x: \
2915  case A##L_x: \
2916  case A##AL_x:
2917 
2918  ATOMIC_MEMORY_SIMPLE_UINT_LIST(SIM_FUNC_B)

2922  AtomicMemorySimpleHelper<int8_t>(instr);
2923  break;
2924  ATOMIC_MEMORY_SIMPLE_UINT_LIST(SIM_FUNC_H)
2925  AtomicMemorySimpleHelper<uint16_t>(instr);
2926  break;
2927  ATOMIC_MEMORY_SIMPLE_INT_LIST(SIM_FUNC_H)
2928  AtomicMemorySimpleHelper<int16_t>(instr);
2929  break;
2930  ATOMIC_MEMORY_SIMPLE_UINT_LIST(SIM_FUNC_w)
2931  AtomicMemorySimpleHelper<uint32_t>(instr);
2932  break;
2933  ATOMIC_MEMORY_SIMPLE_INT_LIST(SIM_FUNC_w)
2934  AtomicMemorySimpleHelper<int32_t>(instr);
2935  break;
2936  ATOMIC_MEMORY_SIMPLE_UINT_LIST(SIM_FUNC_x)
2937  AtomicMemorySimpleHelper<uint64_t>(instr);
2938  break;
2939  ATOMIC_MEMORY_SIMPLE_INT_LIST(SIM_FUNC_x)
2940  AtomicMemorySimpleHelper<int64_t>(instr);
2941  break;
2942  // clang-format on
2943 
2944  case SWPB:
2945  case SWPAB:
2946  case SWPLB:
2947  case SWPALB:
2948  AtomicMemorySwapHelper<uint8_t>(instr);
2949  break;
2950  case SWPH:
2951  case SWPAH:
2952  case SWPLH:
2953  case SWPALH:

2964  case SWPL_x:
2965  case SWPAL_x:

2971 void Simulator::CheckMemoryAccess(uintptr_t address, uintptr_t stack) {
2972  if ((address >= stack_limit_) && (address < stack)) {
2973  fprintf(stream_, "ACCESS BELOW STACK POINTER:\n");
2974  fprintf(stream_, " sp is here: 0x%016" PRIx64 "\n",
2975  static_cast<uint64_t>(stack));
2976  fprintf(stream_, " access was here: 0x%016" PRIx64 "\n",
2977  static_cast<uint64_t>(address));
2978  fprintf(stream_, " stack limit is here: 0x%016" PRIx64 "\n",
2979  static_cast<uint64_t>(stack_limit_));
2980  fprintf(stream_, "\n");
2981  FATAL("ACCESS BELOW STACK POINTER");
2982  }
2983 }

2985 void Simulator::VisitMoveWideImmediate(Instruction* instr) {
2986  MoveWideImmediateOp mov_op =
2987  static_cast<MoveWideImmediateOp>(instr->Mask(MoveWideImmediateMask));
2988  int64_t new_xn_val = 0;
2989 
2990  bool is_64_bits = instr->SixtyFourBits() == 1;
2991  // Shift is limited for W operations.
2992  DCHECK(is_64_bits || (instr->ShiftMoveWide() < 2));
2993 
2994  // Get the shifted immediate.
2995  int64_t shift = instr->ShiftMoveWide() * 16;
2996  int64_t shifted_imm16 = static_cast<int64_t>(instr->ImmMoveWide()) << shift;
2997 
2998  // Compute the new value.
2999  switch (mov_op) {
3000  case MOVN_w:
3001  case MOVN_x: {
3002  new_xn_val = ~shifted_imm16;
3003  if (!is_64_bits) new_xn_val &= kWRegMask;
3004  break;
3005  }
3006  case MOVK_w:
3007  case MOVK_x: {
3008  unsigned reg_code = instr->Rd();
3009  int64_t prev_xn_val = is_64_bits ? xreg(reg_code) : wreg(reg_code);
3010  new_xn_val = (prev_xn_val & ~(INT64_C(0xFFFF) << shift)) | shifted_imm16;
3011  break;
3012  }
3013  case MOVZ_w:
3014  case MOVZ_x: {
3015  new_xn_val = shifted_imm16;
3016  break;
3017  }
3018  default:
3019  UNREACHABLE();
3020  }
3021 
3022  // Update the destination register.
3023  set_xreg(instr->Rd(), new_xn_val);
3024 }
3025 
3026 void Simulator::VisitConditionalSelect(Instruction* instr) {
3027  uint64_t new_val = xreg(instr->Rn());
3028  if (ConditionFailed(static_cast<Condition>(instr->Condition()))) {
3029  new_val = xreg(instr->Rm());
3030  switch (instr->Mask(ConditionalSelectMask)) {
3031  case CSEL_w:
3032  case CSEL_x:
3033  break;
3034  case CSINC_w:
3035  case CSINC_x:
3036  new_val++;
3037  break;
3038  case CSINV_w:
3039  case CSINV_x:
3040  new_val = ~new_val;
3041  break;
3042  case CSNEG_w:
3043  case CSNEG_x:
3044  // Simulate two's complement (instead of casting to signed and negating)
3045  // to avoid undefined behavior on signed overflow.
3046  new_val = (~new_val) + 1;
3047  break;
3048  default:
3049  UNIMPLEMENTED();
3050  }
3051  }
3052  if (instr->SixtyFourBits()) {
3053  set_xreg(instr->Rd(), new_val);
3054  } else {
3055  set_wreg(instr->Rd(), static_cast<uint32_t>(new_val));
3056  }
3057 }

3059 void Simulator::VisitDataProcessing1Source(Instruction* instr) {
3060  unsigned dst = instr->Rd();
3061  unsigned src = instr->Rn();
3062 
3063  switch (instr->Mask(DataProcessing1SourceMask)) {
3064  case RBIT_w:
3065  set_wreg(dst, base::bits::ReverseBits(wreg(src)));
3066  break;
3067  case RBIT_x:
3068  set_xreg(dst, base::bits::ReverseBits(xreg(src)));
3069  break;
3070  case REV16_w:
3071  set_wreg(dst, ReverseBytes(wreg(src), 1));
3072  break;
3073  case REV16_x:
3074  set_xreg(dst, ReverseBytes(xreg(src), 1));
3075  break;
3076  case REV_w:
3077  set_wreg(dst, ReverseBytes(wreg(src), 2));
3078  break;
3079  case REV32_x:
3080  set_xreg(dst, ReverseBytes(xreg(src), 2));
3081  break;
3082  case REV_x:
3083  set_xreg(dst, ReverseBytes(xreg(src), 3));
3084  break;
3085  case CLZ_w:
3086  set_wreg(dst, CountLeadingZeros(wreg(src), kWRegSizeInBits));
3087  break;
3088  case CLZ_x:
3089  set_xreg(dst, CountLeadingZeros(xreg(src), kXRegSizeInBits));
3090  break;
3091  case CLS_w: {
3092  set_wreg(dst, CountLeadingSignBits(wreg(src), kWRegSizeInBits));
3093  break;
3094  }
3095  case CLS_x: {
3096  set_xreg(dst, CountLeadingSignBits(xreg(src), kXRegSizeInBits));
3097  break;
3098  }
3099  case CTZ_w:
3100  set_wreg(dst, CountTrailingZeros(wreg(src), kWRegSizeInBits));
3101  break;
3102  case CTZ_x:
3103  set_xreg(dst, CountTrailingZeros(xreg(src), kXRegSizeInBits));
3104  break;
3105  case CNT_w:
3106  set_wreg(dst, CountSetBits(wreg(src), kWRegSizeInBits));
3107  break;
3108  case CNT_x:
3109  set_xreg(dst, CountSetBits(xreg(src), kXRegSizeInBits));
3110  break;
3111  case ABS_w:
3112  set_wreg(dst, Abs(wreg(src)));
3113  break;
3114  case ABS_x:
3115  set_xreg(dst, Abs(xreg(src)));
3116  break;
3117  default:
3118  UNIMPLEMENTED();
3119  }
3120 }

3122 template <typename T>
3123 void Simulator::DataProcessing2Source(Instruction* instr) {
3124  Shift shift_op = NO_SHIFT;
3125  T result = 0;
3126  switch (instr->Mask(DataProcessing2SourceMask)) {
3127  case SDIV_w:
3128  case SDIV_x: {
3129  T rn = reg<T>(instr->Rn());
3130  T rm = reg<T>(instr->Rm());
3131  if ((rn == std::numeric_limits<T>::min()) && (rm == -1)) {
3132  result = std::numeric_limits<T>::min();
3133  } else if (rm == 0) {
3134  // Division by zero can be trapped, but not on A-class processors.
3135  result = 0;
3136  } else {
3137  result = rn / rm;
3138  }
3139  break;
3140  }
3141  case UDIV_w:
3142  case UDIV_x: {
3143  using unsignedT = std::make_unsigned_t<T>;
3144  unsignedT rn = static_cast<unsignedT>(reg<T>(instr->Rn()));
3145  unsignedT rm = static_cast<unsignedT>(reg<T>(instr->Rm()));
3146  if (rm == 0) {
3147  // Division by zero can be trapped, but not on A-class processors.
3148  result = 0;
3149  } else {
3150  result = rn / rm;
3151  }
3152  break;
3153  }
3154  case LSLV_w:
3155  case LSLV_x:
3156  shift_op = LSL;
3157  break;
3158  case LSRV_w:
3159  case LSRV_x:
3160  shift_op = LSR;
3161  break;
3162  case ASRV_w:
3163  case ASRV_x:
3164  shift_op = ASR;
3165  break;
3166  case RORV_w:
3167  case RORV_x:
3168  shift_op = ROR;
3169  break;
3170  default:
3171  UNIMPLEMENTED();
3172  }
3173 
3174  if (shift_op != NO_SHIFT) {
3175  // Shift distance encoded in the least-significant five/six bits of the
3176  // register.
3177  unsigned shift = wreg(instr->Rm());
3178  if (sizeof(T) == kWRegSize) {
3179  shift &= kShiftAmountWRegMask;
3180  } else {
3181  shift &= kShiftAmountXRegMask;
3182  }
3183  result = ShiftOperand(reg<T>(instr->Rn()), shift_op, shift);
3184  }
3185  set_reg<T>(instr->Rd(), result);
3186 }
3187 
3188 void Simulator::VisitDataProcessing2Source(Instruction* instr) {
3189  if (instr->SixtyFourBits()) {
3190  DataProcessing2Source<int64_t>(instr);
3191  } else {
3192  DataProcessing2Source<int32_t>(instr);
3193  }
3194 }

3196 void Simulator::VisitDataProcessing3Source(Instruction* instr) {
3197  int64_t result = 0;
3198  // Extract and sign- or zero-extend 32-bit arguments for widening operations.
3199  uint64_t rn_u32 = reg<uint32_t>(instr->Rn());
3200  uint64_t rm_u32 = reg<uint32_t>(instr->Rm());
3201  int64_t rn_s32 = reg<int32_t>(instr->Rn());
3202  int64_t rm_s32 = reg<int32_t>(instr->Rm());
3203  switch (instr->Mask(DataProcessing3SourceMask)) {
3204  case MADD_w:
3205  case MADD_x:
3206  result = base::AddWithWraparound(
3207  xreg(instr->Ra()),
3208  base::MulWithWraparound(xreg(instr->Rn()), xreg(instr->Rm())));
3209  break;
3210  case MSUB_w:
3211  case MSUB_x:
3212  result = base::SubWithWraparound(
3213  xreg(instr->Ra()),
3214  base::MulWithWraparound(xreg(instr->Rn()), xreg(instr->Rm())));
3215  break;
3216  case SMADDL_x:
3217  result = base::AddWithWraparound(xreg(instr->Ra()), (rn_s32 * rm_s32));
3218  break;
3219  case SMSUBL_x:
3220  result = base::SubWithWraparound(xreg(instr->Ra()), (rn_s32 * rm_s32));
3221  break;
3222  case UMADDL_x:
3223  result = static_cast<uint64_t>(xreg(instr->Ra())) + (rn_u32 * rm_u32);
3224  break;
3225  case UMSUBL_x:
3226  result = static_cast<uint64_t>(xreg(instr->Ra())) - (rn_u32 * rm_u32);
3227  break;
3228  case SMULH_x:
3229  DCHECK_EQ(instr->Ra(), kZeroRegCode);
3230  result =
3231  base::bits::SignedMulHigh64(xreg(instr->Rn()), xreg(instr->Rm()));
3232  break;
3233  case UMULH_x:
3234  DCHECK_EQ(instr->Ra(), kZeroRegCode);
3235  result =
3236  base::bits::UnsignedMulHigh64(xreg(instr->Rn()), xreg(instr->Rm()));
3237  break;
3238  default:
3239  UNIMPLEMENTED();
3240  }
3241 
3242  if (instr->SixtyFourBits()) {
3243  set_xreg(instr->Rd(), result);
3244  } else {
3245  set_wreg(instr->Rd(), static_cast<int32_t>(result));
3246  }
3247 }

3249 template <typename T>
3250 void Simulator::BitfieldHelper(Instruction* instr) {
3251  using unsignedT = std::make_unsigned_t<T>;
3252  T reg_size = sizeof(T) * 8;
3253  T R = instr->ImmR();
3254  T S = instr->ImmS();
3255  T diff = S - R;
3256  T mask;
3257  if (diff >= 0) {
3258  mask = diff < reg_size - 1 ? (static_cast<unsignedT>(1) << (diff + 1)) - 1
3259  : static_cast<T>(-1);
3260  } else {
3261  uint64_t umask = ((1ULL << (S + 1)) - 1);
3262  umask = (umask >> R) | (umask << (reg_size - R));
3263  mask = static_cast<T>(umask);
3264  diff += reg_size;
3265  }
3266 
3267  // inzero indicates if the extracted bitfield is inserted into the
3268  // destination register value or in zero.
3269  // If extend is true, extend the sign of the extracted bitfield.
3270  bool inzero = false;
3271  bool extend = false;
3272  switch (instr->Mask(BitfieldMask)) {
3273  case BFM_x:
3274  case BFM_w:
3275  break;
3276  case SBFM_x:
3277  case SBFM_w:
3278  inzero = true;
3279  extend = true;
3280  break;
3281  case UBFM_x:
3282  case UBFM_w:
3283  inzero = true;
3284  break;
3285  default:
3286  UNIMPLEMENTED();
3287  }
3288 
3289  T dst = inzero ? 0 : reg<T>(instr->Rd());
3290  T src = reg<T>(instr->Rn());
3291  // Rotate source bitfield into place.
3292  T result = R == 0 ? src
3293  : (static_cast<unsignedT>(src) >> R) |
3294  (static_cast<unsignedT>(src) << (reg_size - R));
3295  // Determine the sign extension.
3296  T topbits_preshift = (static_cast<unsignedT>(1) << (reg_size - diff - 1)) - 1;
3297  T signbits =
3298  diff >= reg_size - 1
3299  ? 0
3300  : ((extend && ((src >> S) & 1) ? topbits_preshift : 0) << (diff + 1));
3301 
3302  // Merge sign extension, dest/zero and bitfield.
3303  result = signbits | (result & mask) | (dst & ~mask);
3304 
3305  set_reg<T>(instr->Rd(), result);
3306 }
3307 
3308 void Simulator::VisitBitfield(Instruction* instr) {
3309  if (instr->SixtyFourBits()) {
3310  BitfieldHelper<int64_t>(instr);
3311  } else {
3312  BitfieldHelper<int32_t>(instr);
3313  }
3314 }

3459  break;
3460 
3461  // A 32-bit input can be handled in the same way as a 64-bit input, since
3462  // the sign- or zero-extension will not affect the conversion.
3463  case SCVTF_dx:
3464  set_dreg(dst, FixedToDouble(xreg(src), 0, round));
3465  break;
3466  case SCVTF_dw:
3467  set_dreg(dst, FixedToDouble(wreg(src), 0, round));
3468  break;
3469  case UCVTF_dx:
3470  set_dreg(dst, UFixedToDouble(xreg(src), 0, round));
3471  break;
3472  case UCVTF_dw: {
3473  set_dreg(dst, UFixedToDouble(reg<uint32_t>(src), 0, round));
3474  break;
3475  }
3476  case SCVTF_sx:
3477  set_sreg(dst, FixedToFloat(xreg(src), 0, round));
3478  break;
3479  case SCVTF_sw:
3480  set_sreg(dst, FixedToFloat(wreg(src), 0, round));
3481  break;
3482  case UCVTF_sx:
3483  set_sreg(dst, UFixedToFloat(xreg(src), 0, round));
3484  break;
3485  case UCVTF_sw: {
3486  set_sreg(dst, UFixedToFloat(reg<uint32_t>(src), 0, round));
3487  break;
3488  }
3489 
3490  default:
3491  UNREACHABLE();
3492  }
3493 }
3494 
3495 void Simulator::VisitFPFixedPointConvert(Instruction* instr) {
3496  AssertSupportedFPCR();
3497 
3498  unsigned dst = instr->Rd();
3499  unsigned src = instr->Rn();
3500  int fbits = 64 - instr->FPScale();
3501 
3502  FPRounding round = fpcr().RMode();
3503 
3504  switch (instr->Mask(FPFixedPointConvertMask)) {
3505  // A 32-bit input can be handled in the same way as a 64-bit input, since
3506  // the sign- or zero-extension will not affect the conversion.
3507  case SCVTF_dx_fixed:
3508  set_dreg(dst, FixedToDouble(xreg(src), fbits, round));
3509  break;
3510  case SCVTF_dw_fixed:
3511  set_dreg(dst, FixedToDouble(wreg(src), fbits, round));
3512  break;
3513  case UCVTF_dx_fixed:
3514  set_dreg(dst, UFixedToDouble(xreg(src), fbits, round));
3515  break;
3516  case UCVTF_dw_fixed: {
3517  set_dreg(dst, UFixedToDouble(reg<uint32_t>(src), fbits, round));
3518  break;
3519  }
3520  case SCVTF_sx_fixed:
3521  set_sreg(dst, FixedToFloat(xreg(src), fbits, round));
3522  break;
3523  case SCVTF_sw_fixed:
3524  set_sreg(dst, FixedToFloat(wreg(src), fbits, round));
3525  break;
3526  case UCVTF_sx_fixed:
3527  set_sreg(dst, UFixedToFloat(xreg(src), fbits, round));
3528  break;
3529  case UCVTF_sw_fixed: {
3530  set_sreg(dst, UFixedToFloat(reg<uint32_t>(src), fbits, round));
3531  break;
3532  }
3533  default:
3534  UNREACHABLE();
3535  }
3536 }
3537 
3538 void Simulator::VisitFPCompare(Instruction* instr) {
3539  AssertSupportedFPCR();
3540 
3541  switch (instr->Mask(FPCompareMask)) {
3542  case FCMP_s:
3543  FPCompare(sreg(instr->Rn()), sreg(instr->Rm()));
3544  break;
3545  case FCMP_d:
3546  FPCompare(dreg(instr->Rn()), dreg(instr->Rm()));
3547  break;
3548  case FCMP_s_zero:
3549  FPCompare(sreg(instr->Rn()), 0.0f);
3550  break;
3551  case FCMP_d_zero:
3552  FPCompare(dreg(instr->Rn()), 0.0);
3553  break;
3554  default:
3555  UNIMPLEMENTED();
3556  }
3557 }
3558 
3559 void Simulator::VisitFPConditionalCompare(Instruction* instr) {
3560  AssertSupportedFPCR();
3561 
3562  switch (instr->Mask(FPConditionalCompareMask)) {
3563  case FCCMP_s:
3564  if (ConditionPassed(static_cast<Condition>(instr->Condition()))) {
3565  FPCompare(sreg(instr->Rn()), sreg(instr->Rm()));
3566  } else {
3567  nzcv().SetFlags(instr->Nzcv());
3568  LogSystemRegister(NZCV);
3569  }
3570  break;
3571  case FCCMP_d: {
3572  if (ConditionPassed(static_cast<Condition>(instr->Condition()))) {
3573  FPCompare(dreg(instr->Rn()), dreg(instr->Rm()));
3574  } else {
3575  // If the condition fails, set the status flags to the nzcv immediate.
3576  nzcv().SetFlags(instr->Nzcv());
3577  LogSystemRegister(NZCV);
3578  }
3579  break;
3580  }
3581  default:
3582  UNIMPLEMENTED();
3583  }
3584 }
3585 
3586 void Simulator::VisitFPConditionalSelect(Instruction* instr) {
3587  AssertSupportedFPCR();
3588 
3589  Instr selected;
3590  if (ConditionPassed(static_cast<Condition>(instr->Condition()))) {
3591  selected = instr->Rn();
3592  } else {
3593  selected = instr->Rm();
3594  }
3595 
3596  switch (instr->Mask(FPConditionalSelectMask)) {
3597  case FCSEL_s:
3598  set_sreg(instr->Rd(), sreg(selected));
3599  break;
3600  case FCSEL_d:
3601  set_dreg(instr->Rd(), dreg(selected));
3602  break;
3603  default:
3604  UNIMPLEMENTED();
3605  }
3606 }

3608 void Simulator::VisitFPDataProcessing1Source(Instruction* instr) {
3609  AssertSupportedFPCR();
3610 
3611  FPRounding fpcr_rounding = static_cast<FPRounding>(fpcr().RMode());
3612  VectorFormat vform = (instr->Mask(FP64) == FP64) ? kFormatD : kFormatS;
3613  SimVRegister& rd = vreg(instr->Rd());
3614  SimVRegister& rn = vreg(instr->Rn());
3615  bool inexact_exception = false;
3616 
3617  unsigned fd = instr->Rd();
3618  unsigned fn = instr->Rn();
3619 
3620  switch (instr->Mask(FPDataProcessing1SourceMask)) {
3621  case FMOV_s:
3622  set_sreg(fd, sreg(fn));
3623  return;
3624  case FMOV_d:
3625  set_dreg(fd, dreg(fn));
3626  return;
3627  case FABS_s:
3628  case FABS_d:
3629  fabs_(vform, vreg(fd), vreg(fn));
3630  // Explicitly log the register update whilst we have type information.
3631  LogVRegister(fd, GetPrintRegisterFormatFP(vform));
3632  return;
3633  case FNEG_s:
3634  case FNEG_d:
3635  fneg(vform, vreg(fd), vreg(fn));
3636  // Explicitly log the register update whilst we have type information.
3637  LogVRegister(fd, GetPrintRegisterFormatFP(vform));
3638  return;
3639  case FCVT_ds:
3640  set_dreg(fd, FPToDouble(sreg(fn)));
3641  return;
3642  case FCVT_sd:
3643  set_sreg(fd, FPToFloat(dreg(fn), FPTieEven));
3644  return;
3645  case FCVT_hs:
3646  set_hreg(fd, FPToFloat16(sreg(fn), FPTieEven));
3647  return;
3648  case FCVT_sh:
3649  set_sreg(fd, FPToFloat(hreg(fn)));
3650  return;
3651  case FCVT_dh:
3652  set_dreg(fd, FPToDouble(FPToFloat(hreg(fn))));
3653  return;
3654  case FCVT_hd:
3655  set_hreg(fd, FPToFloat16(dreg(fn), FPTieEven));
3656  return;
3657  case FSQRT_s:
3658  case FSQRT_d:
3659  fsqrt(vform, rd, rn);
3660  // Explicitly log the register update whilst we have type information.
3661  LogVRegister(fd, GetPrintRegisterFormatFP(vform));
3662  return;
3663  case FRINTI_s:
3664  case FRINTI_d:
3665  break; // Use FPCR rounding mode.
3666  case FRINTX_s:
3667  case FRINTX_d:
3668  inexact_exception = true;
3669  break;
3670  case FRINTA_s:
3671  case FRINTA_d:
3672  fpcr_rounding = FPTieAway;
3673  break;
3674  case FRINTM_s:
3675  case FRINTM_d:
3676  fpcr_rounding = FPNegativeInfinity;
3677  break;
3678  case FRINTN_s:
3679  case FRINTN_d:
3680  fpcr_rounding = FPTieEven;
3681  break;
3682  case FRINTP_s:
3683  case FRINTP_d:
3684  fpcr_rounding = FPPositiveInfinity;
3685  break;
3686  case FRINTZ_s:
3687  case FRINTZ_d:
3688  fpcr_rounding = FPZero;
3689  break;
3690  default:
3691  UNIMPLEMENTED();
3692  }
3693 
3694  // Only FRINT* instructions fall through the switch above.
3695  frint(vform, rd, rn, fpcr_rounding, inexact_exception);
3696  // Explicitly log the register update whilst we have type information
3697  LogVRegister(fd, GetPrintRegisterFormatFP(vform));
3698 }
3699 
3700 void Simulator::VisitFPDataProcessing2Source(Instruction* instr) {
3701  AssertSupportedFPCR();
3702 
3703  VectorFormat vform = (instr->Mask(FP64) == FP64) ? kFormatD : kFormatS;
3704  SimVRegister& rd = vreg(instr->Rd());
3705  SimVRegister& rn = vreg(instr->Rn());
3706  SimVRegister& rm = vreg(instr->Rm());
3707 
3708  switch (instr->Mask(FPDataProcessing2SourceMask)) {
3709  case FADD_s:
3710  case FADD_d:
3711  fadd(vform, rd, rn, rm);
3712  break;
3713  case FSUB_s:
3714  case FSUB_d:
3715  fsub(vform, rd, rn, rm);
3716  break;
3717  case FMUL_s:
3718  case FMUL_d:
3719  fmul(vform, rd, rn, rm);
3720  break;
3721  case FNMUL_s:
3722  case FNMUL_d:
3723  fnmul(vform, rd, rn, rm);
3724  break;
3725  case FDIV_s:
3726  case FDIV_d:
3727  fdiv(vform, rd, rn, rm);
3728  break;
3729  case FMAX_s:
3730  case FMAX_d:
3731  fmax(vform, rd, rn, rm);
3732  break;
3733  case FMIN_s:
3734  case FMIN_d:
3735  fmin(vform, rd, rn, rm);
3736  break;
3737  case FMAXNM_s:
3738  case FMAXNM_d:
3739  fmaxnm(vform, rd, rn, rm);
3740  break;
3741  case FMINNM_s:
3742  case FMINNM_d:
3743  fminnm(vform, rd, rn, rm);
3744  break;
3745  default:
3746  UNREACHABLE();
3747  }
3748  // Explicitly log the register update whilst we have type information.
3749  LogVRegister(instr->Rd(), GetPrintRegisterFormatFP(vform));
3750 }

3752 void Simulator::VisitFPDataProcessing3Source(Instruction* instr) {
3753  AssertSupportedFPCR();
3754 
3755  unsigned fd = instr->Rd();
3756  unsigned fn = instr->Rn();
3757  unsigned fm = instr->Rm();
3758  unsigned fa = instr->Ra();
3759 
3760  switch (instr->Mask(FPDataProcessing3SourceMask)) {
3761  // fd = fa +/- (fn * fm)
3762  case FMADD_s:
3763  set_sreg(fd, FPMulAdd(sreg(fa), sreg(fn), sreg(fm)));
3764  break;
3765  case FMSUB_s:
3766  set_sreg(fd, FPMulAdd(sreg(fa), -sreg(fn), sreg(fm)));
3767  break;
3768  case FMADD_d:
3769  set_dreg(fd, FPMulAdd(dreg(fa), dreg(fn), dreg(fm)));
3770  break;
3771  case FMSUB_d:
3772  set_dreg(fd, FPMulAdd(dreg(fa), -dreg(fn), dreg(fm)));
3773  break;
3774  // Negated variants of the above.
3775  case FNMADD_s:
3776  set_sreg(fd, FPMulAdd(-sreg(fa), -sreg(fn), sreg(fm)));
3777  break;
3778  case FNMSUB_s:
3779  set_sreg(fd, FPMulAdd(-sreg(fa), sreg(fn), sreg(fm)));
3780  break;
3781  case FNMADD_d:
3782  set_dreg(fd, FPMulAdd(-dreg(fa), -dreg(fn), dreg(fm)));
3783  break;
3784  case FNMSUB_d:
3785  set_dreg(fd, FPMulAdd(-dreg(fa), dreg(fn), dreg(fm)));
3786  break;
3787  default:
3788  UNIMPLEMENTED();
3789  }
3790 }

3792 bool Simulator::FPProcessNaNs(Instruction* instr) {
3793  unsigned fd = instr->Rd();
3794  unsigned fn = instr->Rn();
3795  unsigned fm = instr->Rm();
3796  bool done = false;
3797 
3798  if (instr->Mask(FP64) == FP64) {
3799  double result = FPProcessNaNs(dreg(fn), dreg(fm));
3800  if (std::isnan(result)) {
3801  set_dreg(fd, result);
3802  done = true;
3803  }
3804  } else {
3805  float result = FPProcessNaNs(sreg(fn), sreg(fm));
3806  if (std::isnan(result)) {
3807  set_sreg(fd, result);
3808  done = true;
3809  }
3810  }
3811 
3812  return done;
3813 }

3815 // clang-format off
3816 #define PAUTH_SYSTEM_MODES(V) \
3817  V(B1716, 17, xreg(16), kPACKeyIB) \
3818  V(BSP, 30, xreg(31, Reg31IsStackPointer), kPACKeyIB)
3819 // clang-format on

3821 void Simulator::VisitSystem(Instruction* instr) {
3822  // Some system instructions hijack their Op and Cp fields to represent a
3823  // range of immediates instead of indicating a different instruction. This
3824  // makes the decoding tricky.
3825  if (instr->Mask(SystemPAuthFMask) == SystemPAuthFixed) {
3826  // The BType check for PACIBSP happens in CheckBType().
3827  switch (instr->Mask(SystemPAuthMask)) {
3828 #define DEFINE_PAUTH_FUNCS(SUFFIX, DST, MOD, KEY) \
3829  case PACI##SUFFIX: \
3830  set_xreg(DST, AddPAC(xreg(DST), MOD, KEY, kInstructionPointer)); \
3831  break; \
3832  case AUTI##SUFFIX: \
3833  set_xreg(DST, AuthPAC(xreg(DST), MOD, KEY, kInstructionPointer)); \
3834  break;
3835 
3836  PAUTH_SYSTEM_MODES(DEFINE_PAUTH_FUNCS)
3837 #undef DEFINE_PAUTH_FUNCS
3838 #undef PAUTH_SYSTEM_MODES
3839  }
3840  } else if (instr->Mask(SystemSysRegFMask) == SystemSysRegFixed) {
3841  switch (instr->Mask(SystemSysRegMask)) {
3842  case MRS: {
3843  switch (instr->ImmSystemRegister()) {
3844  case NZCV:
3845  set_xreg(instr->Rt(), nzcv().RawValue());
3846  break;
3847  case FPCR:
3848  set_xreg(instr->Rt(), fpcr().RawValue());
3849  break;
3850  default:
3851  UNIMPLEMENTED();
3852  }
3853  break;
3854  }
3855  case MSR: {
3856  switch (instr->ImmSystemRegister()) {
3857  case NZCV:
3858  nzcv().SetRawValue(wreg(instr->Rt()));
3859  LogSystemRegister(NZCV);
3860  break;
3861  case FPCR:
3862  fpcr().SetRawValue(wreg(instr->Rt()));
3863  LogSystemRegister(FPCR);
3864  break;
3865  default:
3866  UNIMPLEMENTED();
3867  }
3868  break;
3869  }
3870  }
3871  } else if (instr->Mask(SystemHintFMask) == SystemHintFixed) {
3872  DCHECK(instr->Mask(SystemHintMask) == HINT);
3873  switch (instr->ImmHint()) {
3874  case NOP:
3875  case YIELD:
3876  case CSDB:
3877  case BTI_jc:
3878  case BTI:
3879  case BTI_c:
3880  case BTI_j:
3881  // The BType checks happen in CheckBType().
3882  break;
3883  default:
3884  UNIMPLEMENTED();
3885  }
3886  } else if (instr->Mask(MemBarrierFMask) == MemBarrierFixed) {
3887  std::atomic_thread_fence(std::memory_order_seq_cst);
3888  } else {
3889  UNIMPLEMENTED();
3890  }
3891 }
3892 
3893 bool Simulator::GetValue(const char* desc, int64_t* value) {
3894  int regnum = CodeFromName(desc);
3895  if (regnum >= 0) {
3896  unsigned code = regnum;
3897  if (code == kZeroRegCode) {
3898  // Catch the zero register and return 0.
3899  *value = 0;
3900  return true;
3901  } else if (code == kSPRegInternalCode) {
3902  // Translate the stack pointer code to 31, for Reg31IsStackPointer.
3903  code = 31;
3904  }
3905  if (desc[0] == 'w') {
3906  *value = wreg(code, Reg31IsStackPointer);
3907  } else {
3908  *value = xreg(code, Reg31IsStackPointer);
3909  }
3910  return true;
3911  } else if (strncmp(desc, "0x", 2) == 0) {
3912  return SScanF(desc + 2, "%" SCNx64, reinterpret_cast<uint64_t*>(value)) ==
3913  1;
3914  } else {
3915  return SScanF(desc, "%" SCNu64, reinterpret_cast<uint64_t*>(value)) == 1;
3916  }
3917 }
3918 
3919 bool Simulator::PrintValue(const char* desc) {
3920  if (strcmp(desc, "sp") == 0) {
3921  DCHECK(CodeFromName(desc) == static_cast<int>(kSPRegInternalCode));
3922  PrintF(stream_, "%s sp:%s 0x%016" PRIx64 "%s\n", clr_reg_name,
3923  clr_reg_value, xreg(31, Reg31IsStackPointer), clr_normal);
3924  return true;
3925  } else if (strcmp(desc, "wsp") == 0) {
3926  DCHECK(CodeFromName(desc) == static_cast<int>(kSPRegInternalCode));
3927  PrintF(stream_, "%s wsp:%s 0x%08" PRIx32 "%s\n", clr_reg_name,
3928  clr_reg_value, wreg(31, Reg31IsStackPointer), clr_normal);
3929  return true;
3930  }
3931 
3932  int i = CodeFromName(desc);
3933  static_assert(kNumberOfRegisters == kNumberOfVRegisters,
3934  "Must be same number of Registers as VRegisters.");
3935  if (i < 0 || static_cast<unsigned>(i) >= kNumberOfVRegisters) return false;
3936 
3937  if (desc[0] == 'v') {
3938  struct qreg_t reg = qreg(i);
3939  PrintF(stream_, "%s %s:%s (%s0x%02x%s", clr_vreg_name, VRegNameForCode(i),
3940  clr_normal, clr_vreg_value, reg.val[0], clr_normal);
3941  for (int b = 1; b < kQRegSize; b++) {
3942  PrintF(stream_, ", %s0x%02x%s", clr_vreg_value, reg.val[b], clr_normal);
3943  }
3944  PrintF(stream_, ")\n");
3945  return true;
3946  } else if (desc[0] == 'd') {
3947  PrintF(stream_, "%s %s:%s %g%s\n", clr_vreg_name, DRegNameForCode(i),
3948  clr_vreg_value, dreg(i), clr_normal);
3949  return true;
3950  } else if (desc[0] == 's') {
3951  PrintF(stream_, "%s %s:%s %g%s\n", clr_vreg_name, SRegNameForCode(i),
3952  clr_vreg_value, sreg(i), clr_normal);
3953  return true;
3954  } else if (desc[0] == 'w') {
3955  PrintF(stream_, "%s %s:%s 0x%08" PRIx32 "%s\n", clr_reg_name,
3956  WRegNameForCode(i), clr_reg_value, wreg(i), clr_normal);
3957  return true;
3958  } else {
3959  // X register names have a wide variety of starting characters, but anything
3960  // else will be an X register.
3961  PrintF(stream_, "%s %s:%s 0x%016" PRIx64 "%s\n", clr_reg_name,
3962  XRegNameForCode(i), clr_reg_value, xreg(i), clr_normal);
3963  return true;
3964  }
3965 }
3966 
3967 void Simulator::Debug() {
3968  if (v8_flags.correctness_fuzzer_suppressions) {
3969  PrintF("Debugger disabled for differential fuzzing.\n");
3970  return;
3971  }
3972  bool done = false;
3973  while (!done) {
3974  // Disassemble the next instruction to execute before doing anything else.
3975  PrintInstructionsAt(pc_, 1);
3976  // Read the command line.
3977  ArrayUniquePtr<char> line(ReadLine("sim> "));
3978  done = ExecDebugCommand(std::move(line));
3979  }
3980 }
3981 
3982 bool Simulator::ExecDebugCommand(ArrayUniquePtr<char> line_ptr) {
3983 #define COMMAND_SIZE 63
3984 #define ARG_SIZE 255
3985 
3986 #define STR(a) #a
3987 #define XSTR(a) STR(a)
3988 
3989  char cmd[COMMAND_SIZE + 1];
3990  char arg1[ARG_SIZE + 1];
3991  char arg2[ARG_SIZE + 1];
3992  char* argv[3] = {cmd, arg1, arg2};
3993 
3994  // Make sure to have a proper terminating character if reaching the limit.
3995  cmd[COMMAND_SIZE] = 0;
3996  arg1[ARG_SIZE] = 0;
3997  arg2[ARG_SIZE] = 0;
3998 
3999  bool cleared_log_disasm_bit = false;
4000 
4001  if (line_ptr == nullptr) return false;
4002 
4003  // Repeat last command by default.
4004  const char* line = line_ptr.get();
4005  const char* last_input = last_debugger_input();
4006  if (strcmp(line, "\n") == 0 && (last_input != nullptr)) {
4007  line_ptr.reset();
4008  line = last_input;
4009  } else {
4010  // Update the latest command ran
4011  set_last_debugger_input(std::move(line_ptr));
4012  }
4013 
4014  // Use sscanf to parse the individual parts of the command line. At the
4015  // moment no command expects more than two parameters.
4016  int argc = SScanF(line,
4017  "%" XSTR(COMMAND_SIZE) "s "
4018  "%" XSTR(ARG_SIZE) "s "
4019  "%" XSTR(ARG_SIZE) "s",
4020  cmd, arg1, arg2);
4021 
4022  // stepi / si ------------------------------------------------------------
4023  if ((strcmp(cmd, "si") == 0) || (strcmp(cmd, "stepi") == 0)) {
4024  // We are about to execute instructions, after which by default we
4025  // should increment the pc_. If it was set when reaching this debug
4026  // instruction, it has not been cleared because this instruction has not
4027  // completed yet. So clear it manually.
4028  pc_modified_ = false;
4029 
4030  if (argc == 1) {
4031  ExecuteInstruction();
4032  } else {
4033  int64_t number_of_instructions_to_execute = 1;
4034  GetValue(arg1, &number_of_instructions_to_execute);
4035 
4036  set_log_parameters(log_parameters() | LOG_DISASM);
4037  while (number_of_instructions_to_execute-- > 0) {
4038  ExecuteInstruction();
4039  }
4040  set_log_parameters(log_parameters() & ~LOG_DISASM);
4041  PrintF("\n");
4042  }
4043 
4044  // If it was necessary, the pc has already been updated or incremented
4045  // when executing the instruction. So we do not want it to be updated
4046  // again. It will be cleared when exiting.
4047  pc_modified_ = true;
4048 
4049  // next / n
4050  // --------------------------------------------------------------
4051  } else if ((strcmp(cmd, "next") == 0) || (strcmp(cmd, "n") == 0)) {
4052  // Tell the simulator to break after the next executed BL.
4053  break_on_next_ = true;
4054  // Continue.
4055  return true;
4056 
4057  // continue / cont / c
4058  // ---------------------------------------------------
4059  } else if ((strcmp(cmd, "continue") == 0) || (strcmp(cmd, "cont") == 0) ||
4060  (strcmp(cmd, "c") == 0)) {
4061  // Leave the debugger shell.
4062  return true;
4063 
4064  // disassemble / disasm / di
4065  // ---------------------------------------------
4066  } else if (strcmp(cmd, "disassemble") == 0 || strcmp(cmd, "disasm") == 0 ||
4067  strcmp(cmd, "di") == 0) {
4068  int64_t n_of_instrs_to_disasm = 10; // default value.
4069  int64_t address = reinterpret_cast<int64_t>(pc_); // default value.
4070  if (argc >= 2) { // disasm <n of instrs>
4071  GetValue(arg1, &n_of_instrs_to_disasm);
4072  }
4073  if (argc >= 3) { // disasm <n of instrs> <address>
4074  GetValue(arg2, &address);
4075  }
4076 
4077  // Disassemble.
4078  PrintInstructionsAt(reinterpret_cast<Instruction*>(address),
4079  n_of_instrs_to_disasm);
4080  PrintF("\n");
4081 
4082  // print / p
4083  // -------------------------------------------------------------
4084  } else if ((strcmp(cmd, "print") == 0) || (strcmp(cmd, "p") == 0)) {
4085  if (argc == 2) {
4086  if (strcmp(arg1, "all") == 0) {
4087  PrintRegisters();
4088  PrintVRegisters();
4089  } else {
4090  if (!PrintValue(arg1)) {
4091  PrintF("%s unrecognized\n", arg1);
4092  }
4093  }
4094  } else {
4095  PrintF(
4096  "print <register>\n"
4097  " Print the content of a register. (alias 'p')\n"
4098  " 'print all' will print all registers.\n"
4099  " Use 'printobject' to get more details about the value.\n");
4100  }
4101 
4102  // printobject / po
4103  // ------------------------------------------------------
4104  } else if ((strcmp(cmd, "printobject") == 0) || (strcmp(cmd, "po") == 0)) {
4105  if (argc == 2) {
4106  int64_t value;
4107  StdoutStream os;
4108  if (GetValue(arg1, &value)) {
4109  Tagged<Object> obj(value);
4110  os << arg1 << ": \n";
4111 #ifdef DEBUG
4112  Print(obj, os);
4113  os << "\n";
4114 #else
4115  os << Brief(obj) << "\n";
4116 #endif
4117  } else {
4118  os << arg1 << " unrecognized\n";
4119  }
4120  } else {
4121  PrintF(
4122  "printobject <value>\n"
4123  "printobject <register>\n"
4124  " Print details about the value. (alias 'po')\n");
4125  }
4126 
4127  // stack / mem
4128  // ----------------------------------------------------------
4129  } else if (strcmp(cmd, "stack") == 0 || strcmp(cmd, "mem") == 0 ||
4130  strcmp(cmd, "dump") == 0) {
4131  int64_t* cur = nullptr;
4132  int64_t* end = nullptr;
4133  int next_arg = 1;
4134 
4135  if (strcmp(cmd, "stack") == 0) {
4136  cur = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(sp());
4137 
4138  } else { // "mem"
4139  int64_t value;
4140  if (!GetValue(arg1, &value)) {
4141  PrintF("%s unrecognized\n", arg1);
4142  return false;
4143  }
4144  cur = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(value);
4145  next_arg++;
4146  }
4147 
4148  int64_t words = 0;
4149  if (argc == next_arg) {
4150  words = 10;
4151  } else if (argc == next_arg + 1) {
4152  if (!GetValue(argv[next_arg], &words)) {
4153  PrintF("%s unrecognized\n", argv[next_arg]);
4154  PrintF("Printing 10 double words by default");
4155  words = 10;
4156  }
4157  } else {
4158  UNREACHABLE();
4159  }
4160  end = cur + words;
4161 
4162  bool skip_obj_print = (strcmp(cmd, "dump") == 0);
4163  while (cur < end) {
4164  PrintF(" 0x%016" PRIx64 ": 0x%016" PRIx64 " %10" PRId64,
4165  reinterpret_cast<uint64_t>(cur), *cur, *cur);
4166  if (!skip_obj_print) {
4167  Tagged<Object> obj(*cur);
4168  Heap* current_heap = isolate_->heap();
4169  if (IsSmi(obj) ||
4170  IsValidHeapObject(current_heap, Cast<HeapObject>(obj))) {
4171  PrintF(" (");
4172  if (IsSmi(obj)) {
4173  PrintF("smi %" PRId32, Smi::ToInt(obj));
4174  } else {
4175  ShortPrint(obj);
4176  }
4177  PrintF(")");
4178  }
4179  }
4180  PrintF("\n");
4181  cur++;
4182  }
4183 
4184  // trace / t
4185  // -------------------------------------------------------------
4186  } else if (strcmp(cmd, "trace") == 0 || strcmp(cmd, "t") == 0) {
4187  if ((log_parameters() & LOG_ALL) != LOG_ALL) {
4188  PrintF("Enabling disassembly, registers and memory write tracing\n");
4189  set_log_parameters(log_parameters() | LOG_ALL);
4190  } else {
4191  PrintF("Disabling disassembly, registers and memory write tracing\n");
4192  set_log_parameters(log_parameters() & ~LOG_ALL);
4193  }
4194 
4195  // break / b
4196  // -------------------------------------------------------------
4197  } else if (strcmp(cmd, "break") == 0 || strcmp(cmd, "b") == 0) {
4198  if (argc == 2) {
4199  int64_t value;
4200  if (GetValue(arg1, &value)) {
4201  SetBreakpoint(reinterpret_cast<Instruction*>(value));
4202  } else {
4203  PrintF("%s unrecognized\n", arg1);
4204  }
4205  } else {
4206  ListBreakpoints();
4207  PrintF("Use `break <address>` to set or disable a breakpoint\n");
4208  }
4209 
4210  // backtrace / bt
4211  // ---------------------------------------------------------------
4212  } else if (strcmp(cmd, "backtrace") == 0 || strcmp(cmd, "bt") == 0) {
4213  Address pc = reinterpret_cast<Address>(pc_);
4214  Address lr = reinterpret_cast<Address>(this->lr());
4215  Address sp = static_cast<Address>(this->sp());
4216  Address fp = static_cast<Address>(this->fp());
4217 
4218  int i = 0;
4219  while (true) {
4220  PrintF("#%d: " V8PRIxPTR_FMT " (sp=" V8PRIxPTR_FMT ", fp=" V8PRIxPTR_FMT
4221  ")\n",
4222  i, pc, sp, fp);
4223  pc = lr;
4224  sp = fp;
4225  if (pc == reinterpret_cast<Address>(kEndOfSimAddress)) {
4226  break;
4227  }
4228  lr = *(reinterpret_cast<Address*>(fp) + 1);
4229  fp = *reinterpret_cast<Address*>(fp);
4230  i++;
4231  if (i > 100) {
4232  PrintF("Too many frames\n");
4233  break;
4234  }
4235  }
4236 
4237  // gdb
4238  // -------------------------------------------------------------------
4239  } else if (strcmp(cmd, "gdb") == 0) {
4240  PrintF("Relinquishing control to gdb.\n");
4241  base::OS::DebugBreak();
4242  PrintF("Regaining control from gdb.\n");
4243 
4244  // sysregs
4245  // ---------------------------------------------------------------
4246  } else if (strcmp(cmd, "sysregs") == 0) {
4247  PrintSystemRegisters();
4248 
4249  // help / h
4250  // --------------------------------------------------------------
4251  } else if (strcmp(cmd, "help") == 0 || strcmp(cmd, "h") == 0) {
4252  PrintF(
4253  "stepi / si\n"
4254  " stepi <n>\n"
4255  " Step <n> instructions.\n"
4256  "next / n\n"
4257  " Continue execution until a BL instruction is reached.\n"
4258  " At this point a breakpoint is set just after this BL.\n"
4259  " Then execution is resumed. It will probably later hit the\n"
4260  " breakpoint just set.\n"
4261  "continue / cont / c\n"
4262  " Continue execution from here.\n"
4263  "disassemble / disasm / di\n"
4264  " disassemble <n> <address>\n"
4265  " Disassemble <n> instructions from current <address>.\n"
4266  " By default <n> is 20 and <address> is the current pc.\n"
4267  "print / p\n"
4268  " print <register>\n"
4269  " Print the content of a register.\n"
4270  " 'print all' will print all registers.\n"
4271  " Use 'printobject' to get more details about the value.\n"
4272  "printobject / po\n"
4273  " printobject <value>\n"
4274  " printobject <register>\n"
4275  " Print details about the value.\n"
4276  "stack\n"
4277  " stack [<words>]\n"
4278  " Dump stack content, default dump 10 words\n"
4279  "mem\n"
4280  " mem <address> [<words>]\n"
4281  " Dump memory content, default dump 10 words\n"
4282  "dump\n"
4283  " dump <address> [<words>]\n"
4284  " Dump memory content without pretty printing JS objects, "
4285  "default dump 10 words\n"
4286  "trace / t\n"
4287  " Toggle disassembly and register tracing\n"
4288  "break / b\n"
4289  " break : list all breakpoints\n"
4290  " break <address> : set / enable / disable a breakpoint.\n"
4291  "backtrace / bt\n"
4292  " Walk the frame pointers, dumping the pc/sp/fp for each frame.\n"
4293  "gdb\n"
4294  " Enter gdb.\n"
4295  "sysregs\n"
4296  " Print all system registers (including NZCV).\n");
4297  } else {
4298  PrintF("Unknown command: %s\n", cmd);
4299  PrintF("Use 'help' for more information.\n");
4300  }
4301 
4302  if (cleared_log_disasm_bit == true) {
4303  set_log_parameters(log_parameters_ | LOG_DISASM);
4304  }
4305  return false;
4306 }
4307 
4308 void Simulator::VisitException(Instruction* instr) {
4309  switch (instr->Mask(ExceptionMask)) {
4310  case HLT: {
4311  if (instr->ImmException() == kImmExceptionIsDebug) {
4312  // Read the arguments encoded inline in the instruction stream.
4313  uint32_t code;
4314  uint32_t parameters;
4315 
4316  memcpy(&code, pc_->InstructionAtOffset(kDebugCodeOffset), sizeof(code));
4317  memcpy(&parameters, pc_->InstructionAtOffset(kDebugParamsOffset),
4318  sizeof(parameters));
4319  char const* message = reinterpret_cast<char const*>(
4320  pc_->InstructionAtOffset(kDebugMessageOffset));
4321 
4322  // Always print something when we hit a debug point that breaks.
4323  // We are going to break, so printing something is not an issue in
4324  // terms of speed.
4325  if (v8_flags.trace_sim_messages || v8_flags.trace_sim ||
4326  (parameters & BREAK)) {
4327  if (message != nullptr) {
4328  PrintF(stream_, "# %sDebugger hit %d: %s%s%s\n", clr_debug_number,
4329  code, clr_debug_message, message, clr_normal);
4330  } else {
4331  PrintF(stream_, "# %sDebugger hit %d.%s\n", clr_debug_number, code,
4332  clr_normal);
4333  }
4334  Builtin maybe_builtin = OffHeapInstructionStream::TryLookupCode(
4335  Isolate::Current(), reinterpret_cast<Address>(pc_));
4336  if (Builtins::IsBuiltinId(maybe_builtin)) {
4337  char const* name = Builtins::name(maybe_builtin);
4338  PrintF(stream_, "# %s %sLOCATION: %s%s\n",
4339  clr_debug_number, clr_debug_message, name, clr_normal);
4340  }
4341  }
4342 
4343  // Other options.
4344  switch (parameters & kDebuggerTracingDirectivesMask) {
4345  case TRACE_ENABLE:
4346  set_log_parameters(log_parameters() | parameters);
4347  if (parameters & LOG_SYS_REGS) {
4348  PrintSystemRegisters();
4349  }
4350  if (parameters & LOG_REGS) {
4351  PrintRegisters();
4352  }
4353  if (parameters & LOG_VREGS) {
4354  PrintVRegisters();
4355  }
4356  break;
4357  case TRACE_DISABLE:
4358  set_log_parameters(log_parameters() & ~parameters);
4359  break;
4360  case TRACE_OVERRIDE:
4361  set_log_parameters(parameters);
4362  break;
4363  default:
4364  // We don't support a one-shot LOG_DISASM.
4365  DCHECK_EQ(parameters & LOG_DISASM, 0);
4366  // Don't print information that is already being traced.
4367  parameters &= ~log_parameters();
4368  // Print the requested information.
4369  if (parameters & LOG_SYS_REGS) PrintSystemRegisters();
4370  if (parameters & LOG_REGS) PrintRegisters();
4371  if (parameters & LOG_VREGS) PrintVRegisters();
4372  }
4373 
4374  // The stop parameters are inlined in the code. Skip them:
4375  // - Skip to the end of the message string.
4376  size_t size = kDebugMessageOffset + strlen(message) + 1;
4377  pc_ = pc_->InstructionAtOffset(RoundUp(size, kInstrSize));
4378  // - Verify that the unreachable marker is present.
4379  DCHECK(pc_->Mask(ExceptionMask) == HLT);
4380  DCHECK_EQ(pc_->ImmException(), kImmExceptionIsUnreachable);
4381  // - Skip past the unreachable marker.
4382  set_pc(pc_->following());
4383 
4384  // Check if the debugger should break.
4385  if (parameters & BREAK) Debug();
4386 
4387  } else if (instr->ImmException() == kImmExceptionIsRedirectedCall) {
4388  DoRuntimeCall(instr);
4389  } else if (instr->ImmException() == kImmExceptionIsPrintf) {
4390  DoPrintf(instr);
4391  } else if (instr->ImmException() == kImmExceptionIsSwitchStackLimit) {
4392  DoSwitchStackLimit(instr);
4393  } else if (instr->ImmException() == kImmExceptionIsUnreachable) {
4394  fprintf(stream_, "Hit UNREACHABLE marker at PC=%p.\n",
4395  reinterpret_cast<void*>(pc_));
4396  abort();
4397 
4398  } else {
4399  base::OS::DebugBreak();
4400  }
4401  break;
4402  }
4403  case BRK:
4404  base::OS::DebugBreak();
4405  break;
4406  default:
4407  UNIMPLEMENTED();
4408  }
4409 }
4410 
4411 void Simulator::VisitNEON2RegMisc(Instruction* instr) {
4412  NEONFormatDecoder nfd(instr);
4413  VectorFormat vf = nfd.GetVectorFormat();
4414 
4415  // Format mapping for "long pair" instructions, [su]addlp, [su]adalp.
4416  static const NEONFormatMap map_lp = {
4417  {23, 22, 30}, {NF_4H, NF_8H, NF_2S, NF_4S, NF_1D, NF_2D}};
4418  VectorFormat vf_lp = nfd.GetVectorFormat(&map_lp);
4419 
4420  static const NEONFormatMap map_fcvtl = {{22}, {NF_4S, NF_2D}};
4421  VectorFormat vf_fcvtl = nfd.GetVectorFormat(&map_fcvtl);
4422 
4423  static const NEONFormatMap map_fcvtn = {{22, 30},
4424  {NF_4H, NF_8H, NF_2S, NF_4S}};
4425  VectorFormat vf_fcvtn = nfd.GetVectorFormat(&map_fcvtn);
4426 
4427  SimVRegister& rd = vreg(instr->Rd());
4428  SimVRegister& rn = vreg(instr->Rn());
4429 
4430  if (instr->Mask(NEON2RegMiscOpcode) <= NEON_NEG_opcode) {
4431  // These instructions all use a two bit size field, except NOT and RBIT,
4432  // which use the field to encode the operation.
4433  switch (instr->Mask(NEON2RegMiscMask)) {
4434  case NEON_REV64:
4435  rev64(vf, rd, rn);
4436  break;
4437  case NEON_REV32:
4438  rev32(vf, rd, rn);
4439  break;
4440  case NEON_REV16:
4441  rev16(vf, rd, rn);
4442  break;
4443  case NEON_SUQADD:
4444  suqadd(vf, rd, rn);
4445  break;
4446  case NEON_USQADD:
4447  usqadd(vf, rd, rn);
4448  break;
4449  case NEON_CLS:
4450  cls(vf, rd, rn);
4451  break;
4452  case NEON_CLZ:
4453  clz(vf, rd, rn);
4454  break;
4455  case NEON_CNT:
4456  cnt(vf, rd, rn);
4457  break;
4458  case NEON_SQABS:
4459  abs(vf, rd, rn).SignedSaturate(vf);
4460  break;
4461  case NEON_SQNEG:
4462  neg(vf, rd, rn).SignedSaturate(vf);
4463  break;
4464  case NEON_CMGT_zero:
4465  cmp(vf, rd, rn, 0, gt);
4466  break;
4467  case NEON_CMGE_zero:
4468  cmp(vf, rd, rn, 0, ge);
4469  break;
4470  case NEON_CMEQ_zero:
4471  cmp(vf, rd, rn, 0, eq);
4472  break;
4473  case NEON_CMLE_zero:
4474  cmp(vf, rd, rn, 0, le);
4475  break;
4476  case NEON_CMLT_zero:
4477  cmp(vf, rd, rn, 0, lt);
4478  break;
4479  case NEON_ABS:
4480  abs(vf, rd, rn);
4481  break;
4482  case NEON_NEG:
4483  neg(vf, rd, rn);
4484  break;
4485  case NEON_SADDLP:
4486  saddlp(vf_lp, rd, rn);
4487  break;
4488  case NEON_UADDLP:
4489  uaddlp(vf_lp, rd, rn);
4490  break;
4491  case NEON_SADALP:
4492  sadalp(vf_lp, rd, rn);
4493  break;
4494  case NEON_UADALP:
4495  uadalp(vf_lp, rd, rn);
4496  break;
4497  case NEON_RBIT_NOT:
4498  vf = nfd.GetVectorFormat(nfd.LogicalFormatMap());
4499  switch (instr->FPType()) {
4500  case 0:
4501  not_(vf, rd, rn);
4502  break;
4503  case 1:
4504  rbit(vf, rd, rn);
4505  break;
4506  default:
4507  UNIMPLEMENTED();
4508  }
4509  break;
4510  }
4511  } else {
4512  VectorFormat fpf = nfd.GetVectorFormat(instr->Mask(NEON2RegMiscHPFixed) ==
4513  NEON2RegMiscHPFixed
4514  ? nfd.FPHPFormatMap()
4515  : nfd.FPFormatMap());
4516  FPRounding fpcr_rounding = static_cast<FPRounding>(fpcr().RMode());
4517  bool inexact_exception = false;
4518 
4519  // These instructions all use a one bit size field, except XTN, SQXTUN,
4520  // SHLL, SQXTN and UQXTN, which use a two bit size field.
4521  switch (instr->Mask(NEON2RegMiscFPMask ^ NEON2RegMiscHPFixed)) {
4522  case NEON_FABS:
4523  fabs_(fpf, rd, rn);
4524  return;
4525  case NEON_FNEG:
4526  fneg(fpf, rd, rn);
4527  return;
4528  case NEON_FSQRT:
4529  fsqrt(fpf, rd, rn);
4530  return;
4531  case NEON_FCVTL:
4532  if (instr->Mask(NEON_Q)) {
4533  fcvtl2(vf_fcvtl, rd, rn);
4534  } else {
4535  fcvtl(vf_fcvtl, rd, rn);
4536  }
4537  return;
4538  case NEON_FCVTN:
4539  if (instr->Mask(NEON_Q)) {
4540  fcvtn2(vf_fcvtn, rd, rn);
4541  } else {
4542  fcvtn(vf_fcvtn, rd, rn);
4543  }
4544  return;
4545  case NEON_FCVTXN:
4546  if (instr->Mask(NEON_Q)) {
4547  fcvtxn2(vf_fcvtn, rd, rn);
4548  } else {
4549  fcvtxn(vf_fcvtn, rd, rn);
4550  }
4551  return;
4552 
4553  // The following instructions break from the switch statement, rather
4554  // than return.
4555  case NEON_FRINTI:
4556  break; // Use FPCR rounding mode.
4557  case NEON_FRINTX:
4558  inexact_exception = true;
4559  break;
4560  case NEON_FRINTA:
4561  fpcr_rounding = FPTieAway;
4562  break;
4563  case NEON_FRINTM:
4564  fpcr_rounding = FPNegativeInfinity;
4565  break;
4566  case NEON_FRINTN:
4567  fpcr_rounding = FPTieEven;
4568  break;
4569  case NEON_FRINTP:
4570  fpcr_rounding = FPPositiveInfinity;
4571  break;
4572  case NEON_FRINTZ:
4573  fpcr_rounding = FPZero;
4574  break;
4575 
4576  // The remaining cases return to the caller.
4577  case NEON_FCVTNS:
4578  fcvts(fpf, rd, rn, FPTieEven);
4579  return;
4580  case NEON_FCVTNU:
4581  fcvtu(fpf, rd, rn, FPTieEven);
4582  return;
4583  case NEON_FCVTPS:
4584  fcvts(fpf, rd, rn, FPPositiveInfinity);
4585  return;
4586  case NEON_FCVTPU:
4587  fcvtu(fpf, rd, rn, FPPositiveInfinity);
4588  return;
4589  case NEON_FCVTMS:
4590  fcvts(fpf, rd, rn, FPNegativeInfinity);
4591  return;
4592  case NEON_FCVTMU:
4593  fcvtu(fpf, rd, rn, FPNegativeInfinity);
4594  return;
4595  case NEON_FCVTZS:
4596  fcvts(fpf, rd, rn, FPZero);
4597  return;
4598  case NEON_FCVTZU:
4599  fcvtu(fpf, rd, rn, FPZero);
4600  return;
4601  case NEON_FCVTAS:
4602  fcvts(fpf, rd, rn, FPTieAway);
4603  return;
4604  case NEON_FCVTAU:
4605  fcvtu(fpf, rd, rn, FPTieAway);
4606  return;
4607  case NEON_SCVTF:
4608  scvtf(fpf, rd, rn, 0, fpcr_rounding);
4609  return;
4610  case NEON_UCVTF:
4611  ucvtf(fpf, rd, rn, 0, fpcr_rounding);
4612  return;
4613  case NEON_URSQRTE:
4614  ursqrte(fpf, rd, rn);
4615  return;
4616  case NEON_URECPE:
4617  urecpe(fpf, rd, rn);
4618  return;
4619  case NEON_FRSQRTE:
4620  frsqrte(fpf, rd, rn);
4621  return;
4622  case NEON_FRECPE:
4623  frecpe(fpf, rd, rn, fpcr_rounding);
4624  return;
4625  case NEON_FCMGT_zero:
4626  fcmp_zero(fpf, rd, rn, gt);
4627  return;
4628  case NEON_FCMGE_zero:
4629  fcmp_zero(fpf, rd, rn, ge);
4630  return;
4631  case NEON_FCMEQ_zero:
4632  fcmp_zero(fpf, rd, rn, eq);
4633  return;
4634  case NEON_FCMLE_zero:
4635  fcmp_zero(fpf, rd, rn, le);
4636  return;
4637  case NEON_FCMLT_zero:
4638  fcmp_zero(fpf, rd, rn, lt);
4639  return;
4640  default:
4641  if ((NEON_XTN_opcode <= instr->Mask(NEON2RegMiscOpcode)) &&
4642  (instr->Mask(NEON2RegMiscOpcode) <= NEON_UQXTN_opcode)) {
4643  switch (instr->Mask(NEON2RegMiscMask)) {
4644  case NEON_XTN:
4645  xtn(vf, rd, rn);
4646  return;
4647  case NEON_SQXTN:
4648  sqxtn(vf, rd, rn);
4649  return;
4650  case NEON_UQXTN:
4651  uqxtn(vf, rd, rn);
4652  return;
4653  case NEON_SQXTUN:
4654  sqxtun(vf, rd, rn);
4655  return;
4656  case NEON_SHLL:
4657  vf = nfd.GetVectorFormat(nfd.LongIntegerFormatMap());
4658  if (instr->Mask(NEON_Q)) {
4659  shll2(vf, rd, rn);
4660  } else {
4661  shll(vf, rd, rn);
4662  }
4663  return;
4664  default:
4665  UNIMPLEMENTED();
4666  }
4667  } else {
4668  UNIMPLEMENTED();
4669  }
4670  }
4671 
4672  // Only FRINT* instructions fall through the switch above.
4673  frint(fpf, rd, rn, fpcr_rounding, inexact_exception);
4674  }
4675 }

4758 void Simulator::VisitNEON3Same(Instruction* instr) {
4759  NEONFormatDecoder nfd(instr);
4760  SimVRegister& rd = vreg(instr->Rd());
4761  SimVRegister& rn = vreg(instr->Rn());
4762  SimVRegister& rm = vreg(instr->Rm());
4763 
4764  if (instr->Mask(NEON3SameLogicalFMask) == NEON3SameLogicalFixed) {
4765  VectorFormat vf = nfd.GetVectorFormat(nfd.LogicalFormatMap());
4766  switch (instr->Mask(NEON3SameLogicalMask)) {
4767  case NEON_AND:
4768  and_(vf, rd, rn, rm);
4769  break;
4770  case NEON_ORR:
4771  orr(vf, rd, rn, rm);
4772  break;
4773  case NEON_ORN:
4774  orn(vf, rd, rn, rm);
4775  break;
4776  case NEON_EOR:
4777  eor(vf, rd, rn, rm);
4778  break;

4784  break;

4790  break;

4814  break;

4816  cmp(vf, rd, rn, rm, hi);
4817  break;

4819  cmp(vf, rd, rn, rm, hs);
4820  break;

4823  break;
4824  case NEON_MLS:
4825  mls(vf, rd, rn, rm);
4826  break;
4827  case NEON_MLA:
4828  mla(vf, rd, rn, rm);
4829  break;
4830  case NEON_MUL:
4831  mul(vf, rd, rn, rm);
4832  break;
4833  case NEON_PMUL:
4834  pmul(vf, rd, rn, rm);
4835  break;

4837  smax(vf, rd, rn, rm);
4838  break;
4839  case NEON_SMAXP:
4840  smaxp(vf, rd, rn, rm);
4841  break;

4843  smin(vf, rd, rn, rm);
4844  break;

4846  sminp(vf, rd, rn, rm);
4847  break;

4850  break;

4853  break;
4854  case NEON_UMAXP:
4855  umaxp(vf, rd, rn, rm);
4856  break;

4858  umin(vf, rd, rn, rm);

4951 void Simulator::VisitNEON3Different(Instruction* instr) {
4952  NEONFormatDecoder nfd(instr);
4953  VectorFormat vf = nfd.GetVectorFormat();
4954  VectorFormat vf_l = nfd.GetVectorFormat(nfd.LongIntegerFormatMap());
4955 
4956  SimVRegister& rd = vreg(instr->Rd());
4957  SimVRegister& rn = vreg(instr->Rn());

4959  int size = instr->NEONSize();
4960 
4961  switch (instr->Mask(NEON3DifferentMask)) {
4962  case NEON_PMULL:
4963  if ((size == 1) || (size == 2)) { // S/D reserved.
4964  VisitUnallocated(instr);

5133 void Simulator::VisitNEON3Extension(Instruction* instr) {
5134  NEONFormatDecoder nfd(instr);
5135  SimVRegister& rd = vreg(instr->Rd());
5136  SimVRegister& rm = vreg(instr->Rm());
5137  SimVRegister& rn = vreg(instr->Rn());
5138  VectorFormat vf = nfd.GetVectorFormat();
5139 
5140  switch (instr->Mask(NEON3ExtensionMask)) {
5141  case NEON_SDOT:
5142  if (vf == kFormat4S || vf == kFormat2S) {
5143  sdot(vf, rd, rn, rm);
5144  } else {
5145  VisitUnallocated(instr);
5146  }
5147 
5148  break;
5149  default:
5150  UNIMPLEMENTED();
5151  }
