5211 void Simulator::VisitNEONByIndexedElement(Instruction* instr) {
5212  NEONFormatDecoder nfd(instr);
5213  VectorFormat vf_r = nfd.GetVectorFormat();
5214  VectorFormat vf = nfd.GetVectorFormat(nfd.LongIntegerFormatMap());
5215 
5216  SimVRegister& rd = vreg(instr->Rd());
5217  SimVRegister& rn = vreg(instr->Rn());
5218 
5219  ByElementOp Op = nullptr;
5220 
5221  int rm_reg = instr->Rm();
5222  int index = (instr->NEONH() << 1) | instr->NEONL();
5223  if (instr->NEONSize() == 1) {
5224  rm_reg &= 0xF;
5225  index = (index << 1) | instr->NEONM();
5226  }
5227 
5228  switch (instr->Mask(NEONByIndexedElementMask)) {
5229  case NEON_MUL_byelement:
5230  Op = &Simulator::mul;
5231  vf = vf_r;
5232  break;
5233  case NEON_MLA_byelement:
5234  Op = &Simulator::mla;
5235  vf = vf_r;
5236  break;
5237  case NEON_MLS_byelement:
5238  Op = &Simulator::mls;
5239  vf = vf_r;
5240  break;
5241  case NEON_SQDMULH_byelement:
5242  Op = &Simulator::sqdmulh;
5243  vf = vf_r;
5244  break;
5245  case NEON_SQRDMULH_byelement:
5246  Op = &Simulator::sqrdmulh;
5247  vf = vf_r;
5248  break;
5249  case NEON_SMULL_byelement:
5250  if (instr->Mask(NEON_Q)) {
5251  Op = &Simulator::smull2;
5252  } else {
5253  Op = &Simulator::smull;
5254  }
5255  break;
5256  case NEON_UMULL_byelement:
5257  if (instr->Mask(NEON_Q)) {
5258  Op = &Simulator::umull2;
5259  } else {
5260  Op = &Simulator::umull;
5261  }
5262  break;
5263  case NEON_SMLAL_byelement:
5264  if (instr->Mask(NEON_Q)) {
5265  Op = &Simulator::smlal2;
5266  } else {
5267  Op = &Simulator::smlal;
5268  }
5269  break;
5270  case NEON_UMLAL_byelement:
5271  if (instr->Mask(NEON_Q)) {
5272  Op = &Simulator::umlal2;
5273  } else {
5274  Op = &Simulator::umlal;
5275  }
5276  break;
5277  case NEON_SMLSL_byelement:
5278  if (instr->Mask(NEON_Q)) {
5279  Op = &Simulator::smlsl2;
5280  } else {
5281  Op = &Simulator::smlsl;
5282  }
5283  break;
5284  case NEON_UMLSL_byelement:
5285  if (instr->Mask(NEON_Q)) {
5286  Op = &Simulator::umlsl2;
5287  } else {
5288  Op = &Simulator::umlsl;
5289  }
5290  break;
5291  case NEON_SQDMULL_byelement:
5292  if (instr->Mask(NEON_Q)) {
5293  Op = &Simulator::sqdmull2;
5294  } else {
5295  Op = &Simulator::sqdmull;
5296  }
5297  break;
5298  case NEON_SQDMLAL_byelement:
5299  if (instr->Mask(NEON_Q)) {
5300  Op = &Simulator::sqdmlal2;
5301  } else {
5302  Op = &Simulator::sqdmlal;
5303  }
5304  break;
5305  case NEON_SQDMLSL_byelement:
5306  if (instr->Mask(NEON_Q)) {
5307  Op = &Simulator::sqdmlsl2;
5308  } else {
5309  Op = &Simulator::sqdmlsl;
5310  }
5311  break;
5312  default:
5313  index = instr->NEONH();
5314  if ((instr->FPType() & 1) == 0) {
5315  index = (index << 1) | instr->NEONL();
5316  }
5317 
5318  vf = nfd.GetVectorFormat(nfd.FPFormatMap());
5319 
5320  switch (instr->Mask(NEONByIndexedElementFPMask)) {
5321  case NEON_FMUL_byelement:
5322  Op = &Simulator::fmul;
5323  break;
5324  case NEON_FMLA_byelement:
5325  Op = &Simulator::fmla;
5326  break;
5327  case NEON_FMLS_byelement:
5328  Op = &Simulator::fmls;
5329  break;
5330  case NEON_FMULX_byelement:
5331  Op = &Simulator::fmulx;
5332  break;
5333  default:
5334  UNIMPLEMENTED();
5335  }
5336  }
5337 
5338  (this->*Op)(vf, rd, rn, vreg(rm_reg), index);
5339 }
5340 
5341 void Simulator::VisitNEONCopy(Instruction* instr) {
5342  NEONFormatDecoder nfd(instr, NEONFormatDecoder::TriangularFormatMap());
5343  VectorFormat vf = nfd.GetVectorFormat();
5344 
5345  SimVRegister& rd = vreg(instr->Rd());
5346  SimVRegister& rn = vreg(instr->Rn());
5347  int imm5 = instr->ImmNEON5();
5348  int lsb = LowestSetBitPosition(imm5);
5349  int reg_index = imm5 >> lsb;
5350 
5351  if (instr->Mask(NEONCopyInsElementMask) == NEON_INS_ELEMENT) {
5352  int imm4 = instr->ImmNEON4();
5353  DCHECK_GE(lsb, 1);
5354  int rn_index = imm4 >> (lsb - 1);
5355  ins_element(vf, rd, reg_index, rn, rn_index);
5356  } else if (instr->Mask(NEONCopyInsGeneralMask) == NEON_INS_GENERAL) {
5357  ins_immediate(vf, rd, reg_index, xreg(instr->Rn()));
5358  } else if (instr->Mask(NEONCopyUmovMask) == NEON_UMOV) {
5359  uint64_t value = LogicVRegister(rn).Uint(vf, reg_index);
5360  value &= MaxUintFromFormat(vf);
5361  set_xreg(instr->Rd(), value);
5362  } else if (instr->Mask(NEONCopyUmovMask) == NEON_SMOV) {
5363  int64_t value = LogicVRegister(rn).Int(vf, reg_index);
5364  if (instr->NEONQ()) {
5365  set_xreg(instr->Rd(), value);
5366  } else {
5367  DCHECK(is_int32(value));
5368  set_wreg(instr->Rd(), static_cast<int32_t>(value));
5369  }
5370  } else if (instr->Mask(NEONCopyDupElementMask) == NEON_DUP_ELEMENT) {
5371  dup_element(vf, rd, rn, reg_index);
5372  } else if (instr->Mask(NEONCopyDupGeneralMask) == NEON_DUP_GENERAL) {
5373  dup_immediate(vf, rd, xreg(instr->Rn()));
5374  } else {
5375  UNIMPLEMENTED();
5376  }
5377 }
5378 
5379 void Simulator::VisitNEONExtract(Instruction* instr) {
5380  NEONFormatDecoder nfd(instr, NEONFormatDecoder::LogicalFormatMap());
5381  VectorFormat vf = nfd.GetVectorFormat();
5382  SimVRegister& rd = vreg(instr->Rd());
5383  SimVRegister& rn = vreg(instr->Rn());
5384  SimVRegister& rm = vreg(instr->Rm());
5385  if (instr->Mask(NEONExtractMask) == NEON_EXT) {
5386  int index = instr->ImmNEONExt();
5387  ext(vf, rd, rn, rm, index);
5388  } else {
5389  UNIMPLEMENTED();
5390  }
5391 }
5392 
5393 void Simulator::NEONLoadStoreMultiStructHelper(const Instruction* instr,
5394  AddrMode addr_mode) {
5395  NEONFormatDecoder nfd(instr, NEONFormatDecoder::LoadStoreFormatMap());
5396  VectorFormat vf = nfd.GetVectorFormat();
5397 
5398  uint64_t addr_base = xreg(instr->Rn(), Reg31IsStackPointer);
5399  int reg_size = RegisterSizeInBytesFromFormat(vf);
5400 
5401  int reg[4];
5402  uint64_t addr[4];
5403  for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
5404  reg[i] = (instr->Rt() + i) % kNumberOfVRegisters;
5405  addr[i] = addr_base + (i * reg_size);
5406  }
5407  int count = 1;
5408  bool log_read = true;
5409 
5410  // Bit 23 determines whether this is an offset or post-index addressing mode.
5411  // In offset mode, bits 20 to 16 should be zero; these bits encode the
5412  // register of immediate in post-index mode.
5413  if ((instr->Bit(23) == 0) && (instr->Bits(20, 16) != 0)) {
5414  UNREACHABLE();
5415  }
5416 
5417  // We use the PostIndex mask here, as it works in this case for both Offset
5418  // and PostIndex addressing.
5419  switch (instr->Mask(NEONLoadStoreMultiStructPostIndexMask)) {
5420  case NEON_LD1_4v:
5421  case NEON_LD1_4v_post:
5422  ld1(vf, vreg(reg[3]), addr[3]);
5423  count++;
5424  [[fallthrough]];
5425  case NEON_LD1_3v:
5426  case NEON_LD1_3v_post:
5427  ld1(vf, vreg(reg[2]), addr[2]);
5428  count++;
5429  [[fallthrough]];
5430  case NEON_LD1_2v:
5431  case NEON_LD1_2v_post:
5432  ld1(vf, vreg(reg[1]), addr[1]);
5433  count++;
5434  [[fallthrough]];
5435  case NEON_LD1_1v:
5436  case NEON_LD1_1v_post:
5437  ld1(vf, vreg(reg[0]), addr[0]);
5438  break;
5439  case NEON_ST1_4v:
5440  case NEON_ST1_4v_post:
5441  st1(vf, vreg(reg[3]), addr[3]);
5442  count++;
5443  [[fallthrough]];
5444  case NEON_ST1_3v:
5445  case NEON_ST1_3v_post:
5446  st1(vf, vreg(reg[2]), addr[2]);
5447  count++;
5448  [[fallthrough]];
5449  case NEON_ST1_2v:
5450  case NEON_ST1_2v_post:
5451  st1(vf, vreg(reg[1]), addr[1]);
5452  count++;
5453  [[fallthrough]];
5454  case NEON_ST1_1v:
5455  case NEON_ST1_1v_post:
5456  st1(vf, vreg(reg[0]), addr[0]);
5457  log_read = false;
5458  break;
5459  case NEON_LD2_post:
5460  case NEON_LD2:
5461  ld2(vf, vreg(reg[0]), vreg(reg[1]), addr[0]);
5462  count = 2;
5463  break;
5464  case NEON_ST2:
5465  case NEON_ST2_post:
5466  st2(vf, vreg(reg[0]), vreg(reg[1]), addr[0]);
5467  count = 2;
5468  log_read = false;
5469  break;
5470  case NEON_LD3_post:
5471  case NEON_LD3:
5472  ld3(vf, vreg(reg[0]), vreg(reg[1]), vreg(reg[2]), addr[0]);
5473  count = 3;
5474  break;
5475  case NEON_ST3:
5476  case NEON_ST3_post:
5477  st3(vf, vreg(reg[0]), vreg(reg[1]), vreg(reg[2]), addr[0]);
5478  count = 3;
5479  log_read = false;
5480  break;
5481  case NEON_LD4_post:
5482  case NEON_LD4:
5483  ld4(vf, vreg(reg[0]), vreg(reg[1]), vreg(reg[2]), vreg(reg[3]), addr[0]);
5484  count = 4;
5485  break;
5486  case NEON_ST4:
5487  case NEON_ST4_post:
5488  st4(vf, vreg(reg[0]), vreg(reg[1]), vreg(reg[2]), vreg(reg[3]), addr[0]);
5489  count = 4;
5490  log_read = false;
5491  break;
5492  default:
5493  UNIMPLEMENTED();
5494  }
5495 
5496  {
5497  GlobalMonitor::SimulatorMutex lock_guard(global_monitor_);
5498  if (log_read) {
5499  local_monitor_.NotifyLoad();
5500  } else {
5501  local_monitor_.NotifyStore();
5502  global_monitor_->NotifyStore_Locked(&global_monitor_processor_);
5503  }
5504  }
5505 
5506  // Explicitly log the register update whilst we have type information.
5507  for (int i = 0; i < count; i++) {
5508  // For de-interleaving loads, only print the base address.
5509  int lane_size = LaneSizeInBytesFromFormat(vf);
5510  PrintRegisterFormat format = GetPrintRegisterFormatTryFP(
5511  GetPrintRegisterFormatForSize(reg_size, lane_size));
5512  if (log_read) {
5513  LogVRead(addr_base, reg[i], format);
5514  } else {
5515  LogVWrite(addr_base, reg[i], format);
5516  }
5517  }
5518 
5519  if (addr_mode == PostIndex) {
5520  int rm = instr->Rm();
5521  // The immediate post index addressing mode is indicated by rm = 31.
5522  // The immediate is implied by the number of vector registers used.
5523  addr_base +=
5524  (rm == 31) ? RegisterSizeInBytesFromFormat(vf) * count : xreg(rm);
5525  set_xreg(instr->Rn(), addr_base, Reg31IsStackPointer);
5526  } else {
5527  DCHECK_EQ(addr_mode, Offset);
5528  }
5529 }
5530 
5531 void Simulator::VisitNEONLoadStoreMultiStruct(Instruction* instr) {
5532  NEONLoadStoreMultiStructHelper(instr, Offset);
5533 }
5534 
5535 void Simulator::VisitNEONLoadStoreMultiStructPostIndex(Instruction* instr) {
5536  NEONLoadStoreMultiStructHelper(instr, PostIndex);
5537 }
5538 
5539 void Simulator::NEONLoadStoreSingleStructHelper(const Instruction* instr,
5540  AddrMode addr_mode) {
5541  uint64_t addr = xreg(instr->Rn(), Reg31IsStackPointer);
5542  int rt = instr->Rt();
5543 
5544  // Bit 23 determines whether this is an offset or post-index addressing mode.
5545  // In offset mode, bits 20 to 16 should be zero; these bits encode the
5546  // register of immediate in post-index mode.
5547  DCHECK_IMPLIES(instr->Bit(23) == 0, instr->Bits(20, 16) == 0);
5548 
5549  bool do_load = false;
5550 
5551  NEONFormatDecoder nfd(instr, NEONFormatDecoder::LoadStoreFormatMap());
5552  VectorFormat vf_t = nfd.GetVectorFormat();
5553 
5554  VectorFormat vf = kFormat16B;
5555  // We use the PostIndex mask here, as it works in this case for both Offset
5556  // and PostIndex addressing.
5557  switch (instr->Mask(NEONLoadStoreSingleStructPostIndexMask)) {
5558  case NEON_LD1_b:
5559  case NEON_LD1_b_post:
5560  case NEON_LD2_b:
5561  case NEON_LD2_b_post:
5562  case NEON_LD3_b:
5563  case NEON_LD3_b_post:
5564  case NEON_LD4_b:
5565  case NEON_LD4_b_post:
5566  do_load = true;
5567  [[fallthrough]];
5568  case NEON_ST1_b:
5569  case NEON_ST1_b_post:
5570  case NEON_ST2_b:
5571  case NEON_ST2_b_post:
5572  case NEON_ST3_b:
5573  case NEON_ST3_b_post:
5574  case NEON_ST4_b:
5575  case NEON_ST4_b_post:
5576  break;
5577 
5578  case NEON_LD1_h:
5579  case NEON_LD1_h_post:
5580  case NEON_LD2_h:
5581  case NEON_LD2_h_post:
5582  case NEON_LD3_h:
5583  case NEON_LD3_h_post:
5584  case NEON_LD4_h:
5585  case NEON_LD4_h_post:
5586  do_load = true;
5587  [[fallthrough]];
5588  case NEON_ST1_h:
5589  case NEON_ST1_h_post:
5590  case NEON_ST2_h:
5591  case NEON_ST2_h_post:
5592  case NEON_ST3_h:
5593  case NEON_ST3_h_post:
5594  case NEON_ST4_h:
5595  case NEON_ST4_h_post:
5596  vf = kFormat8H;
5597  break;
5598 
5599  case NEON_LD1_s:
5600  case NEON_LD1_s_post:
5601  case NEON_LD2_s:
5602  case NEON_LD2_s_post:
5603  case NEON_LD3_s:
5604  case NEON_LD3_s_post:
5605  case NEON_LD4_s:
5606  case NEON_LD4_s_post:
5607  do_load = true;
5608  [[fallthrough]];
5609  case NEON_ST1_s:
5610  case NEON_ST1_s_post:
5611  case NEON_ST2_s:
5612  case NEON_ST2_s_post:
5613  case NEON_ST3_s:
5614  case NEON_ST3_s_post:
5615  case NEON_ST4_s:
5616  case NEON_ST4_s_post: {
5617  static_assert((NEON_LD1_s | (1 << NEONLSSize_offset)) == NEON_LD1_d,
5618  "LSB of size distinguishes S and D registers.");
5619  static_assert(
5620  (NEON_LD1_s_post | (1 << NEONLSSize_offset)) == NEON_LD1_d_post,
5621  "LSB of size distinguishes S and D registers.");
5622  static_assert((NEON_ST1_s | (1 << NEONLSSize_offset)) == NEON_ST1_d,
5623  "LSB of size distinguishes S and D registers.");
5624  static_assert(
5625  (NEON_ST1_s_post | (1 << NEONLSSize_offset)) == NEON_ST1_d_post,
5626  "LSB of size distinguishes S and D registers.");
5627  vf = ((instr->NEONLSSize() & 1) == 0) ? kFormat4S : kFormat2D;
5628  break;
5629  }
5630 
5631  case NEON_LD1R:
5632  case NEON_LD1R_post: {
5633  vf = vf_t;
5634  if (!ProbeMemory(addr, LaneSizeInBytesFromFormat(vf))) return;
5635  ld1r(vf, vreg(rt), addr);
5636  do_load = true;
5637  break;
5638  }
5639 
5640  case NEON_LD2R:
5641  case NEON_LD2R_post: {
5642  vf = vf_t;
5643  if (!ProbeMemory(addr, 2 * LaneSizeInBytesFromFormat(vf))) return;
5644  int rt2 = (rt + 1) % kNumberOfVRegisters;
5645  ld2r(vf, vreg(rt), vreg(rt2), addr);
5646  do_load = true;
5647  break;
5648  }
5649 
5650  case NEON_LD3R:
5651  case NEON_LD3R_post: {
5652  vf = vf_t;
5653  if (!ProbeMemory(addr, 3 * LaneSizeInBytesFromFormat(vf))) return;
5654  int rt2 = (rt + 1) % kNumberOfVRegisters;
5655  int rt3 = (rt2 + 1) % kNumberOfVRegisters;
5656  ld3r(vf, vreg(rt), vreg(rt2), vreg(rt3), addr);
5657  do_load = true;
5658  break;
5659  }
5660 
5661  case NEON_LD4R:
5662  case NEON_LD4R_post: {
5663  vf = vf_t;
5664  if (!ProbeMemory(addr, 4 * LaneSizeInBytesFromFormat(vf))) return;
5665  int rt2 = (rt + 1) % kNumberOfVRegisters;
5666  int rt3 = (rt2 + 1) % kNumberOfVRegisters;
5667  int rt4 = (rt3 + 1) % kNumberOfVRegisters;
5668  ld4r(vf, vreg(rt), vreg(rt2), vreg(rt3), vreg(rt4), addr);
5669  do_load = true;
5670  break;
5671  }
5672  default:
5673  UNIMPLEMENTED();
5674  }
5675 
5676  PrintRegisterFormat print_format =
5677  GetPrintRegisterFormatTryFP(GetPrintRegisterFormat(vf));
5678  // Make sure that the print_format only includes a single lane.
5679  print_format =
5680  static_cast<PrintRegisterFormat>(print_format & ~kPrintRegAsVectorMask);
5681 
5682  int esize = LaneSizeInBytesFromFormat(vf);
5683  int index_shift = LaneSizeInBytesLog2FromFormat(vf);
5684  int lane = instr->NEONLSIndex(index_shift);
5685  int scale = 0;
5686  int rt2 = (rt + 1) % kNumberOfVRegisters;
5687  int rt3 = (rt2 + 1) % kNumberOfVRegisters;
5688  int rt4 = (rt3 + 1) % kNumberOfVRegisters;
5689  switch (instr->Mask(NEONLoadStoreSingleLenMask)) {
5690  case NEONLoadStoreSingle1:
5691  scale = 1;
5692  if (!ProbeMemory(addr, scale * esize)) return;
5693  if (do_load) {
5694  ld1(vf, vreg(rt), lane, addr);
5695  LogVRead(addr, rt, print_format, lane);
5696  } else {
5697  st1(vf, vreg(rt), lane, addr);
5698  LogVWrite(addr, rt, print_format, lane);
5699  }
5700  break;
5701  case NEONLoadStoreSingle2:
5702  scale = 2;
5703  if (!ProbeMemory(addr, scale * esize)) return;
5704  if (do_load) {
5705  ld2(vf, vreg(rt), vreg(rt2), lane, addr);
5706  LogVRead(addr, rt, print_format, lane);
5707  LogVRead(addr + esize, rt2, print_format, lane);
5708  } else {
5709  st2(vf, vreg(rt), vreg(rt2), lane, addr);
5710  LogVWrite(addr, rt, print_format, lane);
5711  LogVWrite(addr + esize, rt2, print_format, lane);
5712  }
5713  break;
5714  case NEONLoadStoreSingle3:
5715  scale = 3;
5716  if (!ProbeMemory(addr, scale * esize)) return;
5717  if (do_load) {
5718  ld3(vf, vreg(rt), vreg(rt2), vreg(rt3), lane, addr);
5719  LogVRead(addr, rt, print_format, lane);
5720  LogVRead(addr + esize, rt2, print_format, lane);
5721  LogVRead(addr + (2 * esize), rt3, print_format, lane);
5722  } else {
5723  st3(vf, vreg(rt), vreg(rt2), vreg(rt3), lane, addr);
5724  LogVWrite(addr, rt, print_format, lane);
5725  LogVWrite(addr + esize, rt2, print_format, lane);
5726  LogVWrite(addr + (2 * esize), rt3, print_format, lane);
5727  }
5728  break;
5729  case NEONLoadStoreSingle4:
5730  scale = 4;
5731  if (!ProbeMemory(addr, scale * esize)) return;
5732  if (do_load) {
5733  ld4(vf, vreg(rt), vreg(rt2), vreg(rt3), vreg(rt4), lane, addr);
5734  LogVRead(addr, rt, print_format, lane);
5735  LogVRead(addr + esize, rt2, print_format, lane);
5736  LogVRead(addr + (2 * esize), rt3, print_format, lane);
5737  LogVRead(addr + (3 * esize), rt4, print_format, lane);
5738  } else {
5739  st4(vf, vreg(rt), vreg(rt2), vreg(rt3), vreg(rt4), lane, addr);
5740  LogVWrite(addr, rt, print_format, lane);
5741  LogVWrite(addr + esize, rt2, print_format, lane);
5742  LogVWrite(addr + (2 * esize), rt3, print_format, lane);
5743  LogVWrite(addr + (3 * esize), rt4, print_format, lane);
5744  }
5745  break;
5746  default:
5747  UNIMPLEMENTED();
5748  }
5749 
5750  {
5751  GlobalMonitor::SimulatorMutex lock_guard(global_monitor_);
5752  if (do_load) {
5753  local_monitor_.NotifyLoad();
5754  } else {
5755  local_monitor_.NotifyStore();
5756  global_monitor_->NotifyStore_Locked(&global_monitor_processor_);
5757  }
5758  }
5759 
5760  if (addr_mode == PostIndex) {
5761  int rm = instr->Rm();
5762  int lane_size = LaneSizeInBytesFromFormat(vf);
5763  set_xreg(instr->Rn(), addr + ((rm == 31) ? (scale * lane_size) : xreg(rm)),
5764  Reg31IsStackPointer);
5765  }
5766 }

5768 void Simulator::VisitNEONLoadStoreSingleStruct(Instruction* instr) {
5769  NEONLoadStoreSingleStructHelper(instr, Offset);
5770 }
5771 
5772 void Simulator::VisitNEONLoadStoreSingleStructPostIndex(Instruction* instr) {
5773  NEONLoadStoreSingleStructHelper(instr, PostIndex);
5774 }
5775 
5776 void Simulator::VisitNEONModifiedImmediate(Instruction* instr) {
5777  SimVRegister& rd = vreg(instr->Rd());
5778  int cmode = instr->NEONCmode();
5779  int cmode_3_1 = (cmode >> 1) & 7;
5780  int cmode_3 = (cmode >> 3) & 1;
5781  int cmode_2 = (cmode >> 2) & 1;
5782  int cmode_1 = (cmode >> 1) & 1;
5783  int cmode_0 = cmode & 1;
5784  int q = instr->NEONQ();
5785  int op_bit = instr->NEONModImmOp();
5786  uint64_t imm8 = instr->ImmNEONabcdefgh();
5787 
5788  // Find the format and immediate value
5789  uint64_t imm = 0;
5790  VectorFormat vform = kFormatUndefined;
5791  switch (cmode_3_1) {
5792  case 0x0:
5793  case 0x1:
5794  case 0x2:
5795  case 0x3:
5796  vform = (q == 1) ? kFormat4S : kFormat2S;
5797  imm = imm8 << (8 * cmode_3_1);
5798  break;
5799  case 0x4:
5800  case 0x5:
5801  vform = (q == 1) ? kFormat8H : kFormat4H;
5802  imm = imm8 << (8 * cmode_1);
5803  break;
5804  case 0x6:
5805  vform = (q == 1) ? kFormat4S : kFormat2S;
5806  if (cmode_0 == 0) {
5807  imm = imm8 << 8 | 0x000000FF;
5808  } else {
5809  imm = imm8 << 16 | 0x0000FFFF;
5810  }
5811  break;
5812  case 0x7:
5813  if (cmode_0 == 0 && op_bit == 0) {
5814  vform = q ? kFormat16B : kFormat8B;
5815  imm = imm8;
5816  } else if (cmode_0 == 0 && op_bit == 1) {
5817  vform = q ? kFormat2D : kFormat1D;
5818  imm = 0;
5819  for (int i = 0; i < 8; ++i) {
5820  if (imm8 & (1ULL << i)) {
5821  imm |= (UINT64_C(0xFF) << (8 * i));
5822  }
5823  }
5824  } else { // cmode_0 == 1, cmode == 0xF.
5825  if (op_bit == 0) {
5826  vform = q ? kFormat4S : kFormat2S;
5827  imm = base::bit_cast<uint32_t>(instr->ImmNEONFP32());
5828  } else if (q == 1) {
5829  vform = kFormat2D;
5830  imm = base::bit_cast<uint64_t>(instr->ImmNEONFP64());
5831  } else {
5832  DCHECK((q == 0) && (op_bit == 1) && (cmode == 0xF));
5833  VisitUnallocated(instr);
5834  }
5835  }
5836  break;
5837  default:
5838  UNREACHABLE();
5839  }
5840 
5841  // Find the operation.
5842  NEONModifiedImmediateOp op;
5843  if (cmode_3 == 0) {
5844  if (cmode_0 == 0) {
5845  op = op_bit ? NEONModifiedImmediate_MVNI : NEONModifiedImmediate_MOVI;
5846  } else { // cmode<0> == '1'
5847  op = op_bit ? NEONModifiedImmediate_BIC : NEONModifiedImmediate_ORR;
5848  }
5849  } else { // cmode<3> == '1'
5850  if (cmode_2 == 0) {
5851  if (cmode_0 == 0) {
5852  op = op_bit ? NEONModifiedImmediate_MVNI : NEONModifiedImmediate_MOVI;
5853  } else { // cmode<0> == '1'
5854  op = op_bit ? NEONModifiedImmediate_BIC : NEONModifiedImmediate_ORR;
5855  }
5856  } else { // cmode<2> == '1'
5857  if (cmode_1 == 0) {
5858  op = op_bit ? NEONModifiedImmediate_MVNI : NEONModifiedImmediate_MOVI;
5859  } else { // cmode<1> == '1'
5860  if (cmode_0 == 0) {
5861  op = NEONModifiedImmediate_MOVI;
5862  } else { // cmode<0> == '1'
5863  op = NEONModifiedImmediate_MOVI;
5864  }
5865  }
5866  }
5867  }
5868 
5869  // Call the logic function.
5870  switch (op) {
5871  case NEONModifiedImmediate_ORR:
5872  orr(vform, rd, rd, imm);
5873  break;
5874  case NEONModifiedImmediate_BIC:
5875  bic(vform, rd, rd, imm);
5876  break;
5877  case NEONModifiedImmediate_MOVI:
5878  movi(vform, rd, imm);
5879  break;
5880  case NEONModifiedImmediate_MVNI:
5881  mvni(vform, rd, imm);
5882  break;
5883  default:
5884  VisitUnimplemented(instr);
5885  }
5886 }
5887 
5888 void Simulator::VisitNEONScalar2RegMisc(Instruction* instr) {
5889  NEONFormatDecoder nfd(instr, NEONFormatDecoder::ScalarFormatMap());
5890  VectorFormat vf = nfd.GetVectorFormat();
5891 
5892  SimVRegister& rd = vreg(instr->Rd());
5893  SimVRegister& rn = vreg(instr->Rn());
5894 
5895  if (instr->Mask(NEON2RegMiscOpcode) <= NEON_NEG_scalar_opcode) {
5896  // These instructions all use a two bit size field, except NOT and RBIT,
5897  // which use the field to encode the operation.
5898  switch (instr->Mask(NEONScalar2RegMiscMask)) {
5899  case NEON_CMEQ_zero_scalar:
5900  cmp(vf, rd, rn, 0, eq);
5901  break;
5902  case NEON_CMGE_zero_scalar:
5903  cmp(vf, rd, rn, 0, ge);
5904  break;
5905  case NEON_CMGT_zero_scalar:
5906  cmp(vf, rd, rn, 0, gt);
5907  break;
5908  case NEON_CMLT_zero_scalar:
5909  cmp(vf, rd, rn, 0, lt);
5910  break;
5911  case NEON_CMLE_zero_scalar:
5912  cmp(vf, rd, rn, 0, le);
5913  break;
5914  case NEON_ABS_scalar:
5915  abs(vf, rd, rn);
5916  break;
5917  case NEON_SQABS_scalar:
5918  abs(vf, rd, rn).SignedSaturate(vf);
5919  break;
5920  case NEON_NEG_scalar:
5921  neg(vf, rd, rn);
5922  break;
5923  case NEON_SQNEG_scalar:
5924  neg(vf, rd, rn).SignedSaturate(vf);
5925  break;
5926  case NEON_SUQADD_scalar:
5927  suqadd(vf, rd, rn);
5928  break;
5929  case NEON_USQADD_scalar:
5930  usqadd(vf, rd, rn);
5931  break;
5932  default:
5933  UNIMPLEMENTED();
5934  }
5935  } else {
5936  VectorFormat fpf = nfd.GetVectorFormat(nfd.FPScalarFormatMap());
5937  FPRounding fpcr_rounding = static_cast<FPRounding>(fpcr().RMode());
5938 
5939  // These instructions all use a one bit size field, except SQXTUN, SQXTN
5940  // and UQXTN, which use a two bit size field.
5941  switch (instr->Mask(NEONScalar2RegMiscFPMask)) {
5942  case NEON_FRECPE_scalar:
5943  frecpe(fpf, rd, rn, fpcr_rounding);
5944  break;
5945  case NEON_FRECPX_scalar:
5946  frecpx(fpf, rd, rn);
5947  break;
5948  case NEON_FRSQRTE_scalar:
5949  frsqrte(fpf, rd, rn);
5950  break;
5951  case NEON_FCMGT_zero_scalar:
5952  fcmp_zero(fpf, rd, rn, gt);
5953  break;
5954  case NEON_FCMGE_zero_scalar:
5955  fcmp_zero(fpf, rd, rn, ge);
5956  break;
5957  case NEON_FCMEQ_zero_scalar:
5958  fcmp_zero(fpf, rd, rn, eq);
5959  break;
5960  case NEON_FCMLE_zero_scalar:
5961  fcmp_zero(fpf, rd, rn, le);
5962  break;
5963  case NEON_FCMLT_zero_scalar:
5964  fcmp_zero(fpf, rd, rn, lt);
5965  break;
5966  case NEON_SCVTF_scalar:
5967  scvtf(fpf, rd, rn, 0, fpcr_rounding);
5968  break;
5969  case NEON_UCVTF_scalar:
5970  ucvtf(fpf, rd, rn, 0, fpcr_rounding);
5971  break;
5972  case NEON_FCVTNS_scalar:
5973  fcvts(fpf, rd, rn, FPTieEven);
5974  break;
5975  case NEON_FCVTNU_scalar:
5976  fcvtu(fpf, rd, rn, FPTieEven);
5977  break;
5978  case NEON_FCVTPS_scalar:
5979  fcvts(fpf, rd, rn, FPPositiveInfinity);
5980  break;
5981  case NEON_FCVTPU_scalar:
5982  fcvtu(fpf, rd, rn, FPPositiveInfinity);
5983  break;
5984  case NEON_FCVTMS_scalar:
5985  fcvts(fpf, rd, rn, FPNegativeInfinity);
5986  break;
5987  case NEON_FCVTMU_scalar:
5988  fcvtu(fpf, rd, rn, FPNegativeInfinity);
5989  break;
5990  case NEON_FCVTZS_scalar:
5991  fcvts(fpf, rd, rn, FPZero);
5992  break;
5993  case NEON_FCVTZU_scalar:
5994  fcvtu(fpf, rd, rn, FPZero);
5995  break;
5996  case NEON_FCVTAS_scalar:
5997  fcvts(fpf, rd, rn, FPTieAway);
5998  break;
5999  case NEON_FCVTAU_scalar:
6000  fcvtu(fpf, rd, rn, FPTieAway);
6001  break;
6002  case NEON_FCVTXN_scalar:
6003  // Unlike all of the other FP instructions above, fcvtxn encodes dest
6004  // size S as size<0>=1. There's only one case, so we ignore the form.
6005  DCHECK_EQ(instr->Bit(22), 1);
6006  fcvtxn(kFormatS, rd, rn);
6007  break;
6008  default:
6009  switch (instr->Mask(NEONScalar2RegMiscMask)) {
6010  case NEON_SQXTN_scalar:
6011  sqxtn(vf, rd, rn);
6012  break;
6013  case NEON_UQXTN_scalar:
6014  uqxtn(vf, rd, rn);
6015  break;
6016  case NEON_SQXTUN_scalar:
6017  sqxtun(vf, rd, rn);
6018  break;
6019  default:
6020  UNIMPLEMENTED();
6021  }
6022  }
6023  }
6024 }

6163 void Simulator::VisitNEONScalarByIndexedElement(Instruction* instr) {
6164  NEONFormatDecoder nfd(instr, NEONFormatDecoder::LongScalarFormatMap());
6165  VectorFormat vf = nfd.GetVectorFormat();
6166  VectorFormat vf_r = nfd.GetVectorFormat(nfd.ScalarFormatMap());
6167 
6168  SimVRegister& rd = vreg(instr->Rd());
6169  SimVRegister& rn = vreg(instr->Rn());
6170  ByElementOp Op = nullptr;
6171 
6172  int rm_reg = instr->Rm();
6173  int index = (instr->NEONH() << 1) | instr->NEONL();
6174  if (instr->NEONSize() == 1) {
6175  rm_reg &= 0xF;
6176  index = (index << 1) | instr->NEONM();
6177  }
6178 
6179  switch (instr->Mask(NEONScalarByIndexedElementMask)) {
6180  case NEON_SQDMULL_byelement_scalar:
6181  Op = &Simulator::sqdmull;
6182  break;
6183  case NEON_SQDMLAL_byelement_scalar:
6184  Op = &Simulator::sqdmlal;
6185  break;
6186  case NEON_SQDMLSL_byelement_scalar:
6187  Op = &Simulator::sqdmlsl;
6188  break;
6189  case NEON_SQDMULH_byelement_scalar:
6190  Op = &Simulator::sqdmulh;
6191  vf = vf_r;
6192  break;
6193  case NEON_SQRDMULH_byelement_scalar:
6194  Op = &Simulator::sqrdmulh;
6195  vf = vf_r;
6196  break;
6197  default:
6198  vf = nfd.GetVectorFormat(nfd.FPScalarFormatMap());
6199  index = instr->NEONH();
6200  if ((instr->FPType() & 1) == 0) {
6201  index = (index << 1) | instr->NEONL();
6202  }
6203  switch (instr->Mask(NEONScalarByIndexedElementFPMask)) {
6204  case NEON_FMUL_byelement_scalar:
6205  Op = &Simulator::fmul;
6206  break;
6207  case NEON_FMLA_byelement_scalar:
6208  Op = &Simulator::fmla;
6209  break;
6210  case NEON_FMLS_byelement_scalar:
6211  Op = &Simulator::fmls;
6212  break;
6213  case NEON_FMULX_byelement_scalar:
6214  Op = &Simulator::fmulx;
6215  break;
6216  default:
6217  UNIMPLEMENTED();
6218  }
6219  }
6220 
6221  (this->*Op)(vf, rd, rn, vreg(rm_reg), index);
6222 }

6271 void Simulator::VisitNEONScalarShiftImmediate(Instruction* instr) {
6272  SimVRegister& rd = vreg(instr->Rd());
6273  SimVRegister& rn = vreg(instr->Rn());
6274  FPRounding fpcr_rounding = static_cast<FPRounding>(fpcr().RMode());
6275 
6276  static const NEONFormatMap map = {
6277  {22, 21, 20, 19},
6278  {NF_UNDEF, NF_B, NF_H, NF_H, NF_S, NF_S, NF_S, NF_S, NF_D, NF_D, NF_D,
6279  NF_D, NF_D, NF_D, NF_D, NF_D}};
6280  NEONFormatDecoder nfd(instr, &map);
6281  VectorFormat vf = nfd.GetVectorFormat();
6282 
6283  int highestSetBit = HighestSetBitPosition(instr->ImmNEONImmh());
6284  int immhimmb = instr->ImmNEONImmhImmb();
6285  int right_shift = (16 << highestSetBit) - immhimmb;
6286  int left_shift = immhimmb - (8 << highestSetBit);
6287  switch (instr->Mask(NEONScalarShiftImmediateMask)) {
6288  case NEON_SHL_scalar:
6289  shl(vf, rd, rn, left_shift);

6296  break;
6297  case NEON_UQSHL_imm_scalar:
6298  uqshl(vf, rd, rn, left_shift);
6299  break;
6300  case NEON_SQSHLU_scalar:
6301  sqshlu(vf, rd, rn, left_shift);
6302  break;
6303  case NEON_SRI_scalar:
6304  sri(vf, rd, rn, right_shift);
6305  break;
6306  case NEON_SSHR_scalar:
6307  sshr(vf, rd, rn, right_shift);
6308  break;
6309  case NEON_USHR_scalar:
6310  ushr(vf, rd, rn, right_shift);
6311  break;
6312  case NEON_SRSHR_scalar:
6313  sshr(vf, rd, rn, right_shift).Round(vf);
6314  break;
6315  case NEON_URSHR_scalar:
6316  ushr(vf, rd, rn, right_shift).Round(vf);
6317  break;
6318  case NEON_SSRA_scalar:
6319  ssra(vf, rd, rn, right_shift);
6320  break;
6321  case NEON_USRA_scalar:
6322  usra(vf, rd, rn, right_shift);
6323  break;
6324  case NEON_SRSRA_scalar:
6325  srsra(vf, rd, rn, right_shift);
6326  break;
6327  case NEON_URSRA_scalar:
6328  ursra(vf, rd, rn, right_shift);
6329  break;
6330  case NEON_UQSHRN_scalar:
6331  uqshrn(vf, rd, rn, right_shift);
6332  break;
6333  case NEON_UQRSHRN_scalar:
6334  uqrshrn(vf, rd, rn, right_shift);
6335  break;
6336  case NEON_SQSHRN_scalar:
6337  sqshrn(vf, rd, rn, right_shift);
6338  break;
6339  case NEON_SQRSHRN_scalar:
6340  sqrshrn(vf, rd, rn, right_shift);
6341  break;
6342  case NEON_SQSHRUN_scalar:
6343  sqshrun(vf, rd, rn, right_shift);
6344  break;
6345  case NEON_SQRSHRUN_scalar:
6346  sqrshrun(vf, rd, rn, right_shift);
6347  break;
6348  case NEON_FCVTZS_imm_scalar:
6349  fcvts(vf, rd, rn, FPZero, right_shift);
6350  break;
6351  case NEON_FCVTZU_imm_scalar:
6352  fcvtu(vf, rd, rn, FPZero, right_shift);
6353  break;
6354  case NEON_SCVTF_imm_scalar:
6355  scvtf(vf, rd, rn, right_shift, fpcr_rounding);
6356  break;
6357  case NEON_UCVTF_imm_scalar:

6365 void Simulator::VisitNEONShiftImmediate(Instruction* instr) {
6366  SimVRegister& rd = vreg(instr->Rd());
6367  SimVRegister& rn = vreg(instr->Rn());
6368  FPRounding fpcr_rounding = static_cast<FPRounding>(fpcr().RMode());
6369 
6370  // 00010->8B, 00011->16B, 001x0->4H, 001x1->8H,
6371  // 01xx0->2S, 01xx1->4S, 1xxx1->2D, all others undefined.
6372  static const NEONFormatMap map = {
6373  {22, 21, 20, 19, 30},
6374  {NF_UNDEF, NF_UNDEF, NF_8B, NF_16B, NF_4H, NF_8H, NF_4H, NF_8H,
6375  NF_2S, NF_4S, NF_2S, NF_4S, NF_2S, NF_4S, NF_2S, NF_4S,
6376  NF_UNDEF, NF_2D, NF_UNDEF, NF_2D, NF_UNDEF, NF_2D, NF_UNDEF, NF_2D,
6377  NF_UNDEF, NF_2D, NF_UNDEF, NF_2D, NF_UNDEF, NF_2D, NF_UNDEF, NF_2D}};
6378  NEONFormatDecoder nfd(instr, &map);
6379  VectorFormat vf = nfd.GetVectorFormat();
6380 
6381  // 0001->8H, 001x->4S, 01xx->2D, all others undefined.
6382  static const NEONFormatMap map_l = {
6383  {22, 21, 20, 19},
6384  {NF_UNDEF, NF_8H, NF_4S, NF_4S, NF_2D, NF_2D, NF_2D, NF_2D}};
6385  VectorFormat vf_l = nfd.GetVectorFormat(&map_l);
6386 
6387  int highestSetBit = HighestSetBitPosition(instr->ImmNEONImmh());
6388  int immhimmb = instr->ImmNEONImmhImmb();
6389  int right_shift = (16 << highestSetBit) - immhimmb;
6390  int left_shift = immhimmb - (8 << highestSetBit);
6391 
6392  switch (instr->Mask(NEONShiftImmediateMask)) {
6393  case NEON_SHL:
6394  shl(vf, rd, rn, left_shift);
6395  break;
6396  case NEON_SLI:
6397  sli(vf, rd, rn, left_shift);
6398  break;
6399  case NEON_SQSHLU:
6400  sqshlu(vf, rd, rn, left_shift);
6401  break;
6402  case NEON_SRI:
6403  sri(vf, rd, rn, right_shift);
6404  break;
6405  case NEON_SSHR:
6406  sshr(vf, rd, rn, right_shift);
6407  break;
6408  case NEON_USHR:
6409  ushr(vf, rd, rn, right_shift);
6410  break;
6411  case NEON_SRSHR:
6412  sshr(vf, rd, rn, right_shift).Round(vf);
6413  break;
6414  case NEON_URSHR:
6415  ushr(vf, rd, rn, right_shift).Round(vf);
6416  break;
6417  case NEON_SSRA:
6418  ssra(vf, rd, rn, right_shift);
6419  break;
6420  case NEON_USRA:
6421  usra(vf, rd, rn, right_shift);
6422  break;
6423  case NEON_SRSRA:
6424  srsra(vf, rd, rn, right_shift);
6425  break;
6426  case NEON_URSRA:
6427  ursra(vf, rd, rn, right_shift);
6428  break;
6429  case NEON_SQSHL_imm:
6430  sqshl(vf, rd, rn, left_shift);
6431  break;
6432  case NEON_UQSHL_imm:
6433  uqshl(vf, rd, rn, left_shift);
6434  break;
6435  case NEON_SCVTF_imm:
6436  scvtf(vf, rd, rn, right_shift, fpcr_rounding);
6437  break;
6438  case NEON_UCVTF_imm:
6439  ucvtf(vf, rd, rn, right_shift, fpcr_rounding);
6440  break;
6441  case NEON_FCVTZS_imm:
6442  fcvts(vf, rd, rn, FPZero, right_shift);
6443  break;
6444  case NEON_FCVTZU_imm:
6445  fcvtu(vf, rd, rn, FPZero, right_shift);
6446  break;
6447  case NEON_SSHLL:
6448  vf = vf_l;
6449  if (instr->Mask(NEON_Q)) {
6450  sshll2(vf, rd, rn, left_shift);
6451  } else {
6452  sshll(vf, rd, rn, left_shift);
6453  }
6454  break;
6455  case NEON_USHLL:
6456  vf = vf_l;
6457  if (instr->Mask(NEON_Q)) {
6458  ushll2(vf, rd, rn, left_shift);
6459  } else {
6460  ushll(vf, rd, rn, left_shift);
6461  }
6462  break;
6463  case NEON_SHRN:
6464  if (instr->Mask(NEON_Q)) {
6465  shrn2(vf, rd, rn, right_shift);
6466  } else {
6467  shrn(vf, rd, rn, right_shift);
6468  }
6469  break;
6470  case NEON_RSHRN:
6471  if (instr->Mask(NEON_Q)) {
6472  rshrn2(vf, rd, rn, right_shift);
6473  } else {
6474  rshrn(vf, rd, rn, right_shift);
6475  }
6476  break;
6477  case NEON_UQSHRN:
6478  if (instr->Mask(NEON_Q)) {
6479  uqshrn2(vf, rd, rn, right_shift);
6480  } else {
6481  uqshrn(vf, rd, rn, right_shift);
6482  }
6483  break;
6484  case NEON_UQRSHRN:
6485  if (instr->Mask(NEON_Q)) {
6486  uqrshrn2(vf, rd, rn, right_shift);
6487  } else {
6488  uqrshrn(vf, rd, rn, right_shift);
6489  }
6490  break;
6491  case NEON_SQSHRN:
6492  if (instr->Mask(NEON_Q)) {
6493  sqshrn2(vf, rd, rn, right_shift);
6494  } else {
6495  sqshrn(vf, rd, rn, right_shift);
6496  }
6497  break;
6498  case NEON_SQRSHRN:
6499  if (instr->Mask(NEON_Q)) {
6500  sqrshrn2(vf, rd, rn, right_shift);
6501  } else {
6502  sqrshrn(vf, rd, rn, right_shift);
6503  }
6504  break;
6505  case NEON_SQSHRUN:
6506  if (instr->Mask(NEON_Q)) {
6507  sqshrun2(vf, rd, rn, right_shift);
6508  } else {
6509  sqshrun(vf, rd, rn, right_shift);
6510  }
6511  break;
6512  case NEON_SQRSHRUN:
6513  if (instr->Mask(NEON_Q)) {
6514  sqrshrun2(vf, rd, rn, right_shift);
6515  } else {
6516  sqrshrun(vf, rd, rn, right_shift);
6517  }
6518  break;
6519  default:
6520  UNIMPLEMENTED();
6521  }
6522 }

6524 void Simulator::VisitNEONTable(Instruction* instr) {
6525  NEONFormatDecoder nfd(instr, NEONFormatDecoder::LogicalFormatMap());
6526  VectorFormat vf = nfd.GetVectorFormat();
6527 
6528  SimVRegister& rd = vreg(instr->Rd());
6529  SimVRegister& rn = vreg(instr->Rn());
6530  SimVRegister& rn2 = vreg((instr->Rn() + 1) % kNumberOfVRegisters);
6531  SimVRegister& rn3 = vreg((instr->Rn() + 2) % kNumberOfVRegisters);
6532  SimVRegister& rn4 = vreg((instr->Rn() + 3) % kNumberOfVRegisters);
6533  SimVRegister& rm = vreg(instr->Rm());
6534 
6535  switch (instr->Mask(NEONTableMask)) {
6536  case NEON_TBL_1v:
6537  tbl(vf, rd, rn, rm);
6538  break;
6539  case NEON_TBL_2v:
6540  tbl(vf, rd, rn, rn2, rm);
6541  break;
6542  case NEON_TBL_3v:
6543  tbl(vf, rd, rn, rn2, rn3, rm);
6544  break;
6545  case NEON_TBL_4v:
6546  tbl(vf, rd, rn, rn2, rn3, rn4, rm);
6547  break;
6548  case NEON_TBX_1v:
6549  tbx(vf, rd, rn, rm);
6550  break;
6551  case NEON_TBX_2v:
6552  tbx(vf, rd, rn, rn2, rm);
6553  break;
6554  case NEON_TBX_3v:
6555  tbx(vf, rd, rn, rn2, rn3, rm);
6556  break;
6557  case NEON_TBX_4v:
6558  tbx(vf, rd, rn, rn2, rn3, rn4, rm);
6559  break;
6560  default:
6561  UNIMPLEMENTED();
6562  }
6563 }

6565 void Simulator::VisitNEONSHA3(Instruction* instr) {
6566  NEONFormatDecoder nfd(instr);
6567  VectorFormat vf = nfd.GetVectorFormat();
6568 
6569  SimVRegister& rd = vreg(instr->Rd());
6570  SimVRegister& rn = vreg(instr->Rn());
6571  SimVRegister& rm = vreg(instr->Rm());
6572  SimVRegister& ra = vreg(instr->Ra());
6573  SimVRegister temp;
6574 
6575  switch (instr->Mask(NEONSHA3Mask)) {
6576  case NEON_BCAX:
6577  bic(vf, temp, rm, ra);
6578  eor(vf, rd, rn, temp);
6579  break;
6580  case NEON_EOR3:
6581  eor(vf, temp, rm, ra);
6582  eor(vf, rd, rn, temp);
6583  break;
6584  default:
6585  UNIMPLEMENTED();
6586  }

6620 void Simulator::DoSwitchStackLimit(Instruction* instr) {
6621  const int64_t stack_limit = xreg(16);
6622  // stack_limit represents js limit and adjusted by extra runaway gap.
6623  // Also, stack switching code reads js_limit generated by
6624  // {Simulator::StackLimit} and then resets it back here.
6625  // So without adjusting back incoming value by safety gap
6626  // {stack_limit_} will be shortened by kAdditionalStackMargin yielding
6627  // positive feedback loop.
6628  SetStackLimit(stack_limit);
6629 }

6631 void Simulator::DoPrintf(Instruction* instr) {
6632  DCHECK((instr->Mask(ExceptionMask) == HLT) &&
6633  (instr->ImmException() == kImmExceptionIsPrintf));
6634 
6635  // Read the arguments encoded inline in the instruction stream.
6636  uint32_t arg_count;
6637  uint32_t arg_pattern_list;
6638  static_assert(sizeof(*instr) == 1);
6639  memcpy(&arg_count, instr + kPrintfArgCountOffset, sizeof(arg_count));
6640  memcpy(&arg_pattern_list, instr + kPrintfArgPatternListOffset,
6641  sizeof(arg_pattern_list));
6642 
6643  DCHECK_LE(arg_count, kPrintfMaxArgCount);
6644  DCHECK_EQ(arg_pattern_list >> (kPrintfArgPatternBits * arg_count), 0);
6645 
6646  // We need to call the host printf function with a set of arguments defined by
6647  // arg_pattern_list. Because we don't know the types and sizes of the
6648  // arguments, this is very difficult to do in a robust and portable way. To
6649  // work around the problem, we pick apart the format string, and print one
6650  // format placeholder at a time.
6651 
6652  // Allocate space for the format string. We take a copy, so we can modify it.
6653  // Leave enough space for one extra character per expected argument (plus the
6654  // '\0' termination).
6655  const char* format_base = reg<const char*>(0);
6656  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(format_base);
6657  size_t length = strlen(format_base) + 1;
6658  char* const format = new char[length + arg_count];
6659 
6660  // A list of chunks, each with exactly one format placeholder.
6661  const char* chunks[kPrintfMaxArgCount];
6662 
6663  // Copy the format string and search for format placeholders.
6664  uint32_t placeholder_count = 0;
6665  char* format_scratch = format;
6666  for (size_t i = 0; i < length; i++) {
6667  if (format_base[i] != '%') {
6668  *format_scratch++ = format_base[i];
6669  } else {
6670  if (format_base[i + 1] == '%') {
6671  // Ignore explicit "%%" sequences.
6672  *format_scratch++ = format_base[i];
6673 
6674  if (placeholder_count == 0) {
6675  // The first chunk is passed to printf using "%s", so we need to
6676  // unescape "%%" sequences in this chunk. (Just skip the next '%'.)
6677  i++;
6678  } else {
6679  // Otherwise, pass through "%%" unchanged.
6680  *format_scratch++ = format_base[++i];
6681  }
6682  } else {
6683  CHECK(placeholder_count < arg_count);
6684  // Insert '\0' before placeholders, and store their locations.
6685  *format_scratch++ = '\0';
6686  chunks[placeholder_count++] = format_scratch;
6687  *format_scratch++ = format_base[i];
6688  }
6689  }
6690  }
6691  DCHECK(format_scratch <= (format + length + arg_count));
6692  CHECK(placeholder_count == arg_count);
6693 
6694  // Finally, call printf with each chunk, passing the appropriate register
6695  // argument. Normally, printf returns the number of bytes transmitted, so we
6696  // can emulate a single printf call by adding the result from each chunk. If
6697  // any call returns a negative (error) value, though, just return that value.
6698 
6699  fprintf(stream_, "%s", clr_printf);
6700 
6701  // Because '\0' is inserted before each placeholder, the first string in
6702  // 'format' contains no format placeholders and should be printed literally.
6703  int result = fprintf(stream_, "%s", format);
6704  int pcs_r = 1; // Start at x1. x0 holds the format string.
6705  int pcs_f = 0; // Start at d0.
6706  if (result >= 0) {
6707  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < placeholder_count; i++) {
6708  int part_result = -1;
6709 
6710  uint32_t arg_pattern = arg_pattern_list >> (i * kPrintfArgPatternBits);
6711  arg_pattern &= (1 << kPrintfArgPatternBits) - 1;
6712  switch (arg_pattern) {
6713  case kPrintfArgW:
6714  part_result = fprintf(stream_, chunks[i], wreg(pcs_r++));
6715  break;
6716  case kPrintfArgX:
6717  part_result = fprintf(stream_, chunks[i], xreg(pcs_r++));
6718  break;
6719  case kPrintfArgD:
6720  part_result = fprintf(stream_, chunks[i], dreg(pcs_f++));
6721  break;
6722  default:
6723  UNREACHABLE();
6724  }
6725 
6726  if (part_result < 0) {
6727  // Handle error values.
6728  result = part_result;
6729  break;
6730  }
6731 
6732  result += part_result;
6733  }
6734  }
6735 
6736  fprintf(stream_, "%s", clr_normal);
6737 
6738 #ifdef DEBUG
6739  CorruptAllCallerSavedCPURegisters();
6740 #endif
6741 
6742  // Printf returns its result in x0 (just like the C library's printf).
6743  set_xreg(0, result);
6744 
6745  // The printf parameters are inlined in the code, so skip them.
6746  set_pc(instr->InstructionAtOffset(kPrintfLength));
6747 
6748  // Set LR as if we'd just called a native printf function.
6749  set_lr(pc());
6750 
6751  delete[] format;
6752 }

6765 void Simulator::LocalMonitor::NotifyLoad() {
6766  if (access_state_ == MonitorAccess::Exclusive) {
6767  // A non exclusive load could clear the local monitor. As a result, it's
6768  // most strict to unconditionally clear the local monitor on load.
6769  Clear();
6770  }
6771 }

6780 void Simulator::LocalMonitor::NotifyStore() {
6781  if (access_state_ == MonitorAccess::Exclusive) {
6782  // A non exclusive store could clear the local monitor. As a result, it's
6783  // most strict to unconditionally clear the local monitor on store.
6784  Clear();
6785  }
6786 }
6787 
6788 bool Simulator::LocalMonitor::NotifyStoreExcl(uintptr_t addr,
6789  TransactionSize size) {
6790  if (access_state_ == MonitorAccess::Exclusive) {
6791  // It is allowed for a processor to require that the address matches
6792  // exactly (B2.10.1), so this comparison does not mask addr.
6793  if (addr == tagged_addr_ && size_ == size) {
6794  Clear();
6795  return true;
6796  } else {
6797  // It is implementation-defined whether an exclusive store to a
6798  // non-tagged address will update memory. As a result, it's most strict
6799  // to unconditionally clear the local monitor.
6800  Clear();
6801  return false;
6802  }
6803  } else {
6804  DCHECK(access_state_ == MonitorAccess::Open);
6805  return false;
6806  }
6807 }

6827 void Simulator::GlobalMonitor::Processor::NotifyStore_Locked(
6828  bool is_requesting_processor) {
6829  if (access_state_ == MonitorAccess::Exclusive) {
6830  // A non exclusive store could clear the global monitor. As a result, it's
6831  // most strict to unconditionally clear global monitors on store.
6832  Clear_Locked();
6833  }
6834 }
6835 
6836 bool Simulator::GlobalMonitor::Processor::NotifyStoreExcl_Locked(
6837  uintptr_t addr, bool is_requesting_processor) {
6838  if (access_state_ == MonitorAccess::Exclusive) {
6839  if (is_requesting_processor) {
6840  // It is allowed for a processor to require that the address matches
6841  // exactly (B2.10.2), so this comparison does not mask addr.
6842  if (addr == tagged_addr_) {
6843  Clear_Locked();
6844  // Introduce occasional stxr failures. This is to simulate the
6845  // behavior of hardware, which can randomly fail due to background
6846  // cache evictions.
6847  if (failure_counter_++ >= kMaxFailureCounter) {
6848  failure_counter_ = 0;
6849  return false;
6850  } else {
6851  return true;
6852  }
6853  }
6854  } else if ((addr & kExclusiveTaggedAddrMask) ==
6855  (tagged_addr_ & kExclusiveTaggedAddrMask)) {
6856  // Check the masked addresses when responding to a successful lock by
6857  // another processor so the implementation is more conservative (i.e. the
6858  // granularity of locking is as large as possible.)
6859  Clear_Locked();
6860  return false;
6861  }
6862  }
6863  return false;
6864 }
6865 
6866 void Simulator::GlobalMonitor::NotifyLoadExcl_Locked(uintptr_t addr,
6867  Processor* processor) {
6868  processor->NotifyLoadExcl_Locked(addr);
6869 }
6870 
6871 void Simulator::GlobalMonitor::NotifyStore_Locked(Processor* processor) {
6872  // Notify each processor of the store operation.
6873  for (Processor* iter = head_; iter; iter = iter->next_) {
6874  bool is_requesting_processor = iter == processor;
6875  iter->NotifyStore_Locked(is_requesting_processor);
6876  }
6877 }
6878 
6879 bool Simulator::GlobalMonitor::NotifyStoreExcl_Locked(uintptr_t addr,
6880  Processor* processor) {
6881  if (processor->NotifyStoreExcl_Locked(addr, true)) {
6882  // Notify the other processors that this StoreExcl succeeded.
6883  for (Processor* iter = head_; iter; iter = iter->next_) {
6884  if (iter != processor) {
6885  iter->NotifyStoreExcl_Locked(addr, false);
6886  }
6887  }
6888  return true;
6889  } else {
6890  return false;
6891  }
6892 }
6893 
6894 void Simulator::GlobalMonitor::PrependProcessor(Processor* processor) {
6895  base::MutexGuard lock_guard(&mutex_);
6896  if (head_) {
6897  head_->prev_ = processor;
6898  }
6899  processor->prev_ = nullptr;
6900  processor->next_ = head_;
6901  head_ = processor;
6902  num_processors_++;
6903 }
6904 
6905 void Simulator::GlobalMonitor::RemoveProcessor(Processor* processor) {
6906  base::MutexGuard lock_guard(&mutex_);
6907  if (processor->prev_) {
6908  processor->prev_->next_ = processor->next_;
6909  } else {
6910  head_ = processor->next_;
6911  }
6912  if (processor->next_) {
6913  processor->next_->prev_ = processor->prev_;
6914  }
6915  processor->prev_ = nullptr;
6916  processor->next_ = nullptr;
6917  num_processors_--;
6918 }

6940 //
6941 // The following functions are used by our gdb macros.
6942 //
6943 V8_DEBUGGING_EXPORT extern bool _v8_internal_Simulator_ExecDebugCommand(
6944  const char* command) {
6945  i::Isolate* isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
6946  if (!isolate) {
6947  fprintf(stderr, "No V8 Isolate found\n");
6948  return false;
6949  }
6950  i::Simulator* simulator = i::Simulator::current(isolate);
6951  if (!simulator) {
6952  fprintf(stderr, "No Arm64 simulator found\n");
6953  return false;
6954  }
6955  // Copy the command so that the simulator can take ownership of it.
6956  size_t len = strlen(command);
6957  i::ArrayUniquePtr<char> command_copy(i::NewArray<char>(len + 1));
6958  i::MemCopy(command_copy.get(), command, len + 1);
6959  return simulator->ExecDebugCommand(std::move(command_copy));
6960 }
